[2025-11-09T22:37:14.828+0000] {python.py:240} INFO - Done. Returned value was: {'recipes': [{'rid': 's_715415', 'title': 'Red Lentil Soup with Chicken and Turnips', 'inst': 'To a large dutch oven or soup pot, heat the olive oil over medium heat. Add the onion, carrots and celery and cook for 8-10 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Add the garlic and cook for an additional 2 minutes, or until fragrant. Season conservatively with a pinch of salt and black pepper.To the pot, add the tomatoes, turnip and red lentils. Stir to combine. Stir in the vegetable stock and increase the heat on the stove to high. Bring the soup to a boil and then reduce to a simmer. Simmer for 20 minutes or until the turnips are tender and the lentils are cooked through. Add the chicken breast and parsley. Cook for an additional 5 minutes. Adjust seasoning to taste. Serve the soup immediately garnished with fresh parsley and any additional toppings. Enjoy!', 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/red-lentil-soup-with-chicken-and-turnips/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'additional toppings: avocado', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'additional toppings: diced avocado, micro greens, chopped basil)'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '3 medium carrots, peeled and diced'}, {'iid': 's_10111143', 'name': 'celery stalks', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 celery stalks, diced'}, {'iid': 's_5064', 'name': 'chicken breast', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups fully-cooked chicken breast, shredded (may be omitted for a vegetarian version)'}, {'iid': 's_10311297', 'name': 'flat leaf parsley', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup flat leaf Italian parsley, chopped (plus extra for garnish)'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '6 cloves of garlic, finely minced'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10011693', 'name': 'canned tomatoes', 'qty': 28.0, 'unit': 'ounce', 'raw': '28 ounce-can plum tomatoes, drained and rinsed, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10016069', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups dried red lentils, rinsed'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and black pepper, to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11564', 'name': 'turnip', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large turnip, peeled and diced'}, {'iid': 's_6615', 'name': 'vegetable stock', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '8 cups vegetable stock'}, {'iid': 's_10511282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium yellow onion, diced'}]}, {'rid': 's_716406', 'title': 'Asparagus and Pea Soup: Real Convenience Food', 'inst': "Chop the garlic and onions. Saute the onions in the EVOO, adding the garlic after a couple of minutes; cook until the onions are translucent. Add the whole bag of asparagus and cover everything with the broth. Season with salt and pepper and a pinch of red pepper flakes, if using.Simmer until the asparagus is bright green and tender (if you've thawed the asparagus it will only take a couple of minutes). Turn off the heat and puree using an immersion blender. Add peas (the heat of the soup will quickly thaw them) and puree until smooth; add more until it reaches the thickness you like.Top with chives and a small dollop of creme fraiche or sour cream or greek yogurt.", 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://fullbellysisters.blogspot.com/2011/03/asparagus-and-pea-soup-real-convenience.html', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11011', 'name': 'asparagus', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bag', 'raw': '1 bag of frozen organic asparagus (preferably thawed)'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'evoo', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '1T EVOO (extra virgin olive oil)'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': 'a couple of garlic cloves'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 onion'}, {'iid': 's_11304', 'name': 'peas', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '2-3c of frozen organic peas'}, {'iid': 's_99253', 'name': 'vegetable broth', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'box', 'raw': '1 box low-sodium vegetable broth'}]}, {'rid': 's_644387', 'title': 'Garlicky Kale', 'inst': 'Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add the kale and cover.Stir occasionally until the volume of the kale is reduced by half. Uncover. Add garlic and basalmic.Allow to cook for about another 30 seconds or so, mixing well so that the garlic and vinegar are well distributed. Serve hot.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/J2FTJBF7/garlicky-kale', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2069', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons balsamic vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'curly kale', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch curly kale, stems removed and chopped'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Olive oil'}]}, {'rid': 's_715446', 'title': 'Slow Cooker Beef Stew', 'inst': "To get started, heat your slow cooker to low. Pour in the cream of mushroom soup, Dale's seasoning, water, and beef broth and stir until mixed well. Add in your stew meat, potatoes, onions, carrots, celery, and green onions. Stir well until covered and cook on low for 8 hours. You can add salt and pepper as desired, but the flavors and the Dale's marry together so well that you probably won’t need them.", 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/slow-cooker-beef-stew-recipe/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_6008', 'name': 'beef broth', 'qty': 14.5, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 14.5oz can of Beef Broth'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '2 large carrots, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11143', 'name': 'celery', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'stalks', 'raw': '2 stalks celery, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_6147', 'name': 'cream of mushroom soup', 'qty': 26.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 26oz can Cream of Mushroom Soup'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'green onions', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 green onions, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10211352', 'name': 'new potatoes', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '10 new (red)potatoes'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small onion chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1042027', 'name': "dale's seasoning", 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': "½ cup Dale's Seasoning"}, {'iid': 's_10023618', 'name': 'stew meat', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '2 pounds stew meat'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups water'}]}, {'rid': 's_782601', 'title': 'Red Kidney Bean Jambalaya', 'inst': 'Rinse the kidney beans and brown rice separately. Cover the kidney beans with water and soak for 8 hours or overnight. In a separate bowl, cover the brown rice with water and soak for 8 hours or overnight. Drain and rinse the kidney beans, then transfer to a medium saucepan and cover with fresh water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer for 1 hour or until just tender but not falling apart. Drain and set aside. Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. When hot, add the onion and saut for 5 minutes. Now add the garlic, carrots, celery and green beans, and stir for another 5 minutes. Next add the tomatoes, red pepper, eggplant, sage, thyme, marjoram and celery seed, and continue to stir for another few minutes. Pour in the vegetable stock, liquid smoke, rice and the cooked kidney beans. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to medium low, cover, and cook, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes or until the rice is tender. Add water as necessary if the stew becomes too dry.Season with sriracha, salt and pepper, and taste for seasoning  add more liquid smoke, sriracha, salt, pepper or herbs as desired.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodandspice.com/2016/05/red-kidney-bean-jambalaya.html', 'cui': 'cajun', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_20041', 'name': 'brown rice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2/3 cup dried brown rice (2 cups cooked)'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '2 medium carrots, sliced'}, {'iid': 's_11143', 'name': 'celery', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'stalks', 'raw': '2 stalks celery, sliced'}, {'iid': 's_2007', 'name': 'celery seed', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon celery seed'}, {'iid': 's_16032', 'name': 'kidney beans', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2/3 cup dried kidney beans (2 cups cooked)'}, {'iid': 's_1002023', 'name': 'marjoram', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon dried marjoram'}, {'iid': 's_2042', 'name': 'thyme', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons dried thyme'}, {'iid': 's_11209', 'name': 'eggplant', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium eggplant, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic, minced or crushed'}, {'iid': 's_11052', 'name': 'green beans', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'handfuls', 'raw': '3 handfuls of green beans, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'fresh ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1012038', 'name': 'ground sage', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons ground sage'}, {'iid': 's_93627', 'name': 'liquid smoke', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 to 1 teaspoon liquid smoke, to taste'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 red bell pepper, seeded and chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small white or red onion, diced'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '1 1/2 teaspoons sea salt, or to taste'}, {'iid': 's_6168', 'name': 'sriracha', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon sriracha or other hot sauce'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '2 medium tomatoes, diced'}, {'iid': 's_6615', 'name': 'vegetable stock', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '3 cups vegetable stock'}]}, {'rid': 's_716426', 'title': 'Cauliflower, Brown Rice, and Vegetable Fried Rice', 'inst': 'Remove the cauliflower\'s tough stem and reserve for another use. Using a food processor, pulse cauliflower florets until they resemble rice or couscous. You should end up with around four cups of "cauliflower rice." Heat 1T butter and 1T oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add garlic and the white and light green pieces of scallion. Sauté about a minute. Add the cauliflower to the pan. Stir to coat with oil, then spread out in pan and let sit; you want it cook a bit and to caramelize (get a bit brown), which will bring out the sweetness. After a couple of minutes, stir and spread out again. Add cold rice (it separates easily, so it won\'t clump up during cooking), plus the additional grapeseed and coconut oil or butter. Raise heat to medium-high. Toss everything together and, again, spread the mixture out over the whole pan and press a bit into the bottom. Let it sit for about two minutes—so the rice can get toasted and a little crispy. Add the peas and broccoli and stir again. Drizzle soy sauce and toasted sesame oil over rice.Cook for another minute or so and turn off heat. Add chopped scallion tops and toss.I like to toast some sesame seeds in a dry pan; I sprinkle these and some more raw, chopped scallion over the top of the rice for added flavor and crunch.Season to taste with salt and, if you\'d like, more soy sauce. Keep in mind that if you\'re serving this with something salty and saucy (ie. teriyaki chicken) you may want to hold off on adding too much salt to the fried rice.', 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://fullbellysisters.blogspot.com/2012/01/cauliflower-fried-rice-more-veggies.html', 'cui': 'chinese', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_4517', 'name': 'grapeseed oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons grapeseed oil'}, {'iid': 's_4047', 'name': 'coconut oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons coconut oil'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'scallions', 'qty': 7.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '7 scallions, chopped (keep white/light green ends separate from dark green tops)'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '5 cloves of garlic, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11135', 'name': 'cauliflower', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'head', 'raw': 'head of cauliflower, raw'}, {'iid': 's_20041', 'name': 'brown rice', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '3 cups of cooked brown rice, cold'}, {'iid': 's_11090', 'name': 'broccoli', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups cooked broccoli, chopped small'}, {'iid': 's_11304', 'name': 'peas', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup frozen peas'}, {'iid': 's_16424', 'name': 'soy sauce', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '3 T reduced-sodium soy sauce'}, {'iid': 's_4058', 'name': 'sesame oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons toasted sesame oil'}, {'iid': 's_12023', 'name': 'sesame seeds', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'toasted sesame seeds, optional'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'additional scallion tops', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'additional chopped scallion tops for garnish'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt, to taste'}]}, {'rid': 's_716004', 'title': 'Quinoa and Chickpea Salad with Sun-Dried Tomatoes and Dried Cherries', 'inst': 'Rinse the quinoa and soak for 8 hours or overnight in 2 cups of water. Rinse the chickpeas and soak for 8 hours or overnight in several inches of water.Rinse the chickpeas and transfer to a small saucepan. Cover with fresh water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer for 1 hour or until buttery soft.While the chickpeas are cooking, soak the sun-dried tomatoes in hot water for 30 minutes, then drain and chop. Meanwhile, bring the quinoa to a boil in a medium saucepan. Reduce heat to the lowest setting, cover, and simmer for 15 minutes or until the water is absorbed. Remove from heat and wait 5 minutes before fluffing with a fork.Meanwhile, toast the cashews in a dry unoiled skillet or saucepan over medium-low heat, tossing or stirring frequently, for 10 minutes until browned. Transfer the chickpeas, quinoa, sun-dried tomatoes, cashews and dried cherries to a large mixing bowl. Whisk the dressing ingredients together and pour over the salad. Stir to combine and serve at room temperature or chilled.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodandspice.com/2016/01/quinoa-and-chickpea-salad-with-sun.html', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_12087', 'name': 'cashews', 'qty': 0.33333334, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/3 cup raw cashews, chopped or left whole'}, {'iid': 's_93822', 'name': 'dried cherries', 'qty': 0.33333334, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/3 cup dried cherries'}, {'iid': 's_16056', 'name': 'dried chickpeas', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1/2 cup dried chickpeas (1 1/2 cups cooked or 1 14 oz can)'}, {'iid': 's_2042', 'name': 'dried thyme', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon dried thyme'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'ground cumin', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon ground cumin'}, {'iid': 's_19296', 'name': 'honey', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '1 1/2 tablespoons honey'}, {'iid': 's_9206', 'name': 'juice of orange', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 medium orange, juiced'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 cup dried quinoa (2 cups cooked)'}, {'iid': 's_1022068', 'name': 'red wine vinegar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons red wine vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea-salt', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'sea salt and fresh cracked black pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11955', 'name': 'sun-dried tomatoes', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup sun-dried tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_2043', 'name': 'turmeric', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon turmeric'}]}, {'rid': 's_716627', 'title': 'Easy Homemade Rice and Beans', 'inst': 'Heat the olive oil in a large pot over medium heat. Add onions and saute until soft, or for about 5 minutes. Add all other remaining ingredients and stir together. Increase the heat to medium high and bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat to medium low so that the mixture simmers. Cook for 15-20 minutes, or until rice is fluffy and liquid is absorbed.* Serve with salsa, cheese, and sour cream.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'http://cooking2perfection.blogspot.com/2012/11/easy-homemade-rice-and-beans.html', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_16018', 'name': 'black beans', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'ounce', 'raw': '1 15-ounce can black beans, not drained'}, {'iid': 's_10011693', 'name': 'canned tomatoes', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': 'ounce', 'raw': '1 10-ounce can Rotel tomatoes with diced green chilies, not drained'}, {'iid': 's_2009', 'name': 'chili powder', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp chili powder'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'cumin', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/2 tsp cumin'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/4 tsp ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_6168', 'name': 'optional: of hot sauce', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'dashes', 'raw': 'optional: 4-5 dashes of hot sauce'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup onion, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_20444', 'name': 'rice', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup uncooked rice'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '3 Tbsp water'}]}, {'rid': 's_664147', 'title': 'Tuscan White Bean Soup with Olive Oil and Rosemary', 'inst': 'Rinse the beans thoroughly and place them in a 7-quart slow cooker along with the water, onion, garlic, and bay leaf. Cover and cook on LOW for about 8 hours, or until the beans are nice and tender. Remove the bay leaf. Using a handheld immersion blender, puree the remaining ingredients to the desired texture. Add the salt to taste.Ladle the soup into bowls. Drizzle with the olive oil, sprinkle with rosemary, and serve.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/HPKTNKY5/tuscan-white-bean-soup-with-olive-oil-and-rosemary', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2004', 'name': 'bay leaf', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 bay leaf'}, {'iid': 's_2063', 'name': 'rosemary', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon chopped fresh rosemary'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '6 cloves garlic'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium onion, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons water'}, {'iid': 's_10316049', 'name': 'beans', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups dried white beans, such as great northern or cannellini'}]}, {'rid': 's_640941', 'title': 'Crunchy Brussels Sprouts Side Dish', 'inst': 'Blanch the Brussels sprouts in boiling water for 6-8 minutes or in a microwave oven in a little water for about 4 minutes. Drain. Saute the Brussels sprouts, stirring constantly, until they become golden-brown in color.Meanwhile mix the vinegar, mustard, honey and olive oil. Add walnuts to the sprouts, stir and combine. Pour the vinegar dressing over the sprouts, season with pepper. Mix and combine so that each sprout is covered with the dressing. Serve warm or cold as a side dish.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/LKJMG5RP/crunchy-brussels-sprouts', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '¼ tsp black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11098', 'name': 'brussels sprouts', 'qty': 800.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '800 g Brussels sprouts, trimmed (or 1 kg untrimmed)'}, {'iid': 's_1032046', 'name': 'dijon mustard', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp Dijon mustard'}, {'iid': 's_19296', 'name': 'honey', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp of honey'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '3 Tbs olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_1022068', 'name': 'red wine vinegar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '2 Tbs red wine vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_12155', 'name': 'walnuts', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '¼ cup walnuts, toasted, coarsely chopped'}]}, {'rid': 's_660306', 'title': 'Slow Cooker: Pork and Garbanzo Beans', 'inst': 'In slow cooker layer in this order: pork, then garbanzo beans, onion, pour water over all. Mix spices together and sprinkle over pork and beans. Cover. Set on low and cook for approximately 6 hours. The beans should be tender and creamy. The pork should fall very easily from the bone. The pork can be either shredded for cubed for your preference. *3Serving Suggestion: Scoop about 1 cup of beans with broth into a soup bowl. Top with shredded pork. Add 1/4 of an avocado sliced, top with chopped fresh cilantro.NOTES:*1 The beans do not need to be soaked before adding to the slow cooker. They will be perfectly soft and creamy without pre-soaking.*2 Substitute the water for: 2 cups water and 1 bottle of good quality dark beer like Negra Modelo. You can also substitute the water for chicken stock or pork stock. Each of these substitutions will add an extra dimension of flavor.*3 If you want to shred the pork, it is easiest to do when the pork is hot. Use two forks to pull the pork apart and shred. If you want to slice the pork (like for sandwiches) it is best to do when the pork is cold. Let the pork rest in the refrigerator for several hours or over night. Slice with a serrated knife or a very sharp chef knife.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/6BFKWQ7C/slow-cooker-pork-and-garbanzo-beans', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2010', 'name': 'cinnamon', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp cinnamon'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'cumin', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 Tbsp dried cumin'}, {'iid': 's_16056', 'name': 'garbanzo beans *1', 'qty': 16.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '16 oz bag of dried garbanzo beans (rinsed, but not soaked) *1'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small onion, sliced'}, {'iid': 's_10010225', 'name': 'pork should roast', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '3lb Pork Should Roast – bone-in'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp salt'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water *2', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '4 cups of water (also see “Notes” at bottom of recipe) *2'}]}, {'rid': 's_756814', 'title': 'Powerhouse Almond Matcha Superfood Smoothie', 'inst': 'Combine all of the ingredients in a blender. Blend on high until smooth. Serve immediately.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/blog/2015/05/17/powehouse-almond-matcha-superfood-smoothie', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_12195', 'name': 'natural almond butter', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons unsalted natural almond butter'}, {'iid': 's_93607', 'name': 'almond milk', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups unsweetened almond milk'}, {'iid': 's_9040', 'name': 'banana', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium frozen banana'}, {'iid': 's_12006', 'name': 'chia seeds', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons chia seeds'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'baby kale', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup baby kale, packed'}, {'iid': 's_9176', 'name': 'mango pieces', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup frozen mango pieces'}, {'iid': 's_98932', 'name': 'matcha tea powder', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon matcha green tea powder'}, {'iid': 's_9266', 'name': 'pineapple', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '3/4 cup frozen pineapple'}, {'iid': 's_2050', 'name': 'vanilla extract', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract'}]}, {'rid': 's_715769', 'title': 'Broccolini Quinoa Pilaf', 'inst': 'In a large pan with lid heat olive oil over medium high heat. Add onions and cook for 1 minute. Add garlic and cook until onions are translucent and garlic is fragrant. Add quinoa to pan, stir to combine. Slowly add in broth and bring to a boil.Cover and reduce heat to low, cook for 15 minutes.In the last 2-3 minutes of cooking add in broccolini on top of the quinoa (do not stir) and cover.Uncover and toss broccolini and quinoa together.Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add walnuts and serve hot.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://pickfreshfoods.com/broccolini-quinoa-pilaf/', 'cui': 'mediterranean', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_98840', 'name': 'broccolini', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch broccolini, trimmed'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic clove', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 garlic clove, minced'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup onion'}, {'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup quinoa, rinsed'}, {'iid': 's_6615', 'name': 'vegetable broth', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups vegetable broth'}, {'iid': 's_10112155', 'name': 'walnuts', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '2 oz chopped walnuts'}]}, {'rid': 's_642129', 'title': 'Easy To Make Spring Rolls', 'inst': 'Have all the ingredients ready for assembly. In a large bowl filled with water, dip a wrapper in the water. The rice wrapper will begin to soften and this is your cue to remove it from the water and lay it flat. Place 2 shrimp halves in a row across the center and top with basil, mint, cilantro and lettuce. Leave about 1 to 2 inches uncovered on each side.  Fold uncovered sides inward, then tightly roll the wrapper, beginning at the end with the lettuce.  Repeat with remaining wrappers and ingredients. Cut and serve at room temperature with dipping sauce.The Culinary Chases Note: The rice wrapper can be fussy to handle if you let it soak too long. I usually give it a couple of swishes in the water and then remove. It may feel slightly stiff but by the time you are ready to roll up, the wrapper will become very pliable.  A typical spring roll contains cooked rice vermicelli, slivers of cooked pork and julienned carrots but you can use whatever suits your fancy.  Enjoy!', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/B5HHJWNP/easy-to-make-spring-rolls', 'cui': 'vietnamese', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'you can use regular basil', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup Thai basil or you can use regular basil'}, {'iid': 's_11250', 'name': 'boston lettuce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small head', 'raw': 'small head of Boston lettuce, roughly chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11819', 'name': 'chili pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': 'small chili pepper, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_6179', 'name': 'fish sauce', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup fish sauce'}, {'iid': 's_2012', 'name': 'coriander leaves', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup coriander (cilantro) leaves'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic'}, {'iid': 's_9160', 'name': 'lime juice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons fresh lime juice'}, {'iid': 's_2064', 'name': 'mint leaves', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup mint leaves'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'red bell pepper, thinly sliced'}, {'iid': 's_1022053', 'name': 'rice vinegar', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup rice vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_15270', 'name': 'shrimp', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '8 large cooked shrimp, slice in half lengthways'}, {'iid': 's_10118368', 'name': 'spring roll wrappers', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': '8-inch', 'raw': '8 large (8-inch) spring roll wrappers'}, {'iid': 's_19335', 'name': 'sugar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon sugar'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup water'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'nuoc cham', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Nuoc Cham (dipping sauce)'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'nuoc cham', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Nuoc Cham (dipping sauce)'}]}, {'rid': 's_642605', 'title': 'Farro With Mushrooms and Asparagus', 'inst': 'In a small bowl, cover dried mushrooms with warm water.  Soak for 25 minutes, or until softened. Drain the mushrooms, and discard the soaking water.  Chop finely.Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add farro, and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain and reserve.In a large skillet, over medium heat, heat the olive oil, and add onion, garlic, thyme, and mushrooms.Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes or until onions are tender.Stir in 2 tablespoons of sherry vinegar, and continue cooking for 1 minute. Add chicken stock, and bring it to a boil.Stir in farro, and return to a boil.Lower the heat to a simmer, and cover with a tight fitting lid.  Cook for 10 minutes. Add asparagus, and cook, covered, for an additional 10 minutes.Season with 1 tablespoon sherry vinegar, salt and pepper.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/DMV5G8FD/farro-with-mushrooms-and-asparagus', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11011', 'name': 'asparagus', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch asparagus, cut into ¼ pieces'}, {'iid': 's_6172', 'name': 'chicken stock', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups chicken stock'}, {'iid': 's_10011268', 'name': 'porcini mushrooms', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'ounce', 'raw': '1 ounce dried porcini mushrooms'}, {'iid': 's_10020005', 'name': 'farro', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '8 ounces farro'}, {'iid': 's_1012049', 'name': 'thyme', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon chopped fresh thyme'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves of garlic, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium onion, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper, to taste'}, {'iid': 's_1012068', 'name': 'sherry vinegar', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons sherry vinegar'}]}, {'rid': 's_636589', 'title': 'Butternut Squash Frittata', 'inst': 'Preheat oven to 350Spray a 10 oz oven safe dish with cooking spray Add your butternut squash In a measuring cup add your eggs and milk. Mix until combined. Pour over butternut squash. Sprinkle with pepper and top with cheese. Bake in oven for 30-35 minutes, until middle is slightly firm Let it cool for a few minutes', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/XQXFKGHT/butternut-squash-frittata', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11485', 'name': 'butternut squash', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large butternut squash, peeled, seeded, thinly sliced (with a mandoline)'}, {'iid': 's_1159', 'name': 'goat cheese', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1/2 oz goat cheese'}, {'iid': 's_1226', 'name': 'liquid egg substitute', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup liquid egg substitute'}, {'iid': 's_1085', 'name': 'non-fat milk', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 tbsp. non-fat milk'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'serving', 'raw': 'Pepper to taste'}]}, {'rid': 's_646738', 'title': "Herbivoracious' White Bean and Kale Soup", 'inst': 'PRESSURE COOKER METHOD In the pressure cooker base, but without pressure, heat the olive oil over medium-high heat. Saut the onion, garlic, carrot, and 1 teaspoon salt until the onion is translucent, about 4 minutes. Add the bay leaves, rosemary, and your choice(s) of the Parmesan rind, dried porcini, or broth powder. Add the dry beans and water. Bring up to high pressure and cook for 40 minutes, then allow the pressure to release naturally. Open the lid. Remove the bay leaves and Parmesan rind, if using. Add the kale and lemon juice and simmer for 10 minutes, until the kale is tender. Taste and adjust the seasoning, then serve, garnished with a generous drizzle of extra-virgin olive oil. STOVETOP METHOD Cover the beans with several inches of water and soak overnight. Drain the beans and place in a large saucepan. Cover with water by at least 2 inches and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer the beans until tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Drain the beans, reserving the bean broth. In a large saucepan, heat the olive oil over medium-high heat. Saut the onion, garlic, carrot, and 1 teaspoon salt until the onion is translucent, about 4 minutes. Add 4 cups of the bean broth, the bay leaves, rosemary, and your choice of the Parmesan rind, dried porcini, or broth powder. Bring to a simmer and cook for 30 minutes. Remove the bay leaves and Parmesan rind, if using. Add the beans, kale, and lemon juice and simmer for 10 minutes, until the kale is tender. Taste and adjust the seasoning, then serve, garnished with a generous drizzle of extra-virgin olive oil.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/YX5XP75N/herbivoracious-white-bean-and-kale-soup', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil, plus additional for garnish'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium onion, finely diced'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'head', 'raw': '1 whole head garlic, peeled and minced'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrot', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 carrot, finely diced'}, {'iid': 's_1082047', 'name': 'kosher salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon kosher salt'}, {'iid': 's_2004', 'name': 'bay leaves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 bay leaves'}, {'iid': 's_2063', 'name': 'rosemary leaves', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon minced fresh rosemary leaves'}, {'iid': 's_10011268', 'name': 'the following: parmesan rind)', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 or more of the following: 1 Parmesan rind or 3/4 ounce dried porcini mushrooms or 2 tablespoons vegetable broth powder (gluten-free if needed)'}, {'iid': 's_10316049', 'name': 'navy', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups dried white beans such as cannellini or navy, rinsed and picked over'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 7.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '7 cups water'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'dinosaur kale', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch dinosaur (lacinato) kale, stems stripped and discarded, leaves cut into ribbons and thoroughly washed'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'Juice of 1 lemon'}]}, {'rid': 's_663559', 'title': 'Tomato and lentil soup', 'inst': 'Saut onion and garlic in olive oil for 5 minutes. Add the carrot, saut for another 2 minutes. Add tomatoes, bay leaf and water, stir and bring to the boil. Stir in lentils, season with salt and cook for 5 minutes. Before serving sprinkle with chopped parsley.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/5V4PTMT2/tomato-and-lentil-soup', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '2 Tbs olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 onion, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 carrots cut into cubes'}, {'iid': 's_11531', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 480.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '480g canned chopped tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_2004', 'name': 'bay leaf', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 bay leaf'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 1.3, 'unit': 'l', 'raw': '1.3 l water'}, {'iid': 's_10316069', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 250.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '250 g lentils'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '¼ tsp salt'}, {'iid': 's_11297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch chopped parsley'}]}, {'rid': 's_662670', 'title': 'Swiss Chard Wraps', 'inst': 'Chop off the stems of the swiss chard at the point where it meets the leaf. You could stem the swiss chard entirely. I like leaving a bit of stem with the leaves to give better structure to the wraps. Chop the cauliflower into small pieces and pulse them in a food processor until it looks like rice. I usually pulse the cauliflower florets and the stalk together. Place the olive oil in a saut pan over medium-high heat. Once the pan is hot, add the garlic and let it fry for about a minute or two, or until the garlic starts to brown. Add the pulsed cauliflower rice and cook it for about 2-3 minutes. The cauliflower should turn into a vibrant yellow-orange color when it is cooked. Add a pinch of salt and chopped basil to the cauliflower and stir. Spiralize the zucchini with Blade B to create zucchini noodles. If you do not have a spiralizer, just create zucchini ribbons with a vegetable peeler. To assemble the wraps, place a large leaf flat down. Add a bit of sauted cauliflower, zucchini noodles, red pepper, and avocado along the swiss chard stalk. Drizzle a bit of vinaigrette on top of the vegetables and wrap everything up. Enjoy these wraps as a side to your favorite protein! Feel free to dip these wraps in more sauce. These wraps are best consumed when they are freshly made. Refrigerate any leftovers in an airtight container.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/LHXZRNVW/swiss-chard-wraps', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11147', 'name': 'swiss chard leaves', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '6-7 large swiss chard leaves, rinsed and dried'}, {'iid': 's_9200', 'name': 'orange cauliflower', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small head', 'raw': '1 small head of orange cauliflower'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1 1/2 Tbs olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '3 cloves garlic, pressed or minced'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of salt'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'sprig', 'raw': '1 sprig of fresh basil, leaves finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11477', 'name': 'zucchini', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium zucchini (courgette)'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large red pepper, thinly sliced'}, {'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium avocado, sliced'}, {'iid': 's_16091', 'name': "trader joe's spicy peanut vinaigrette", 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': "3-4 Tbs Trader Joe's Asian Style Spicy Peanut Vinaigrette (or your favorite sauce)"}]}, {'rid': 's_640062', 'title': 'Corn Avocado Salsa', 'inst': 'Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Spread corn flat on a baking sheet.Spray lightly with olive oil spray.Roast corn in the oven for about 8-10 minutes. (Be careful not to brown too much or burn.) Remove from heat and allow to cool.Finely chop red pepper and garlic and mix in a bowl.Peel and coarsely chop avocado and add to bowl. Add cooled corn. Mix in cumin and vinegar and blend well.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/BDRS2JZG/corn-avocado-salsa', 'cui': 'mexican', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 Avocado'}, {'iid': 's_2069', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon Balsamic vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'cumin', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon Cumin'}, {'iid': 's_11913', 'name': 'corn', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '3/4 cup Corn, freshly hulled (You can also use frozen corn, thawed)'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1/2 medium Red Pepper'}]}, {'rid': 's_715421', 'title': 'Cheesy Chicken Enchilada Quinoa Casserole', 'inst': "To get started, heat your oven to 350 and prepare an 8x8 baking dish. Cook the quinoa according to the instructions. If you haven't already, boil and shred your chicken breast.In a medium sized mixing bowl add 2 Tbsp cilantro, 1 cup shredded cheese, quinoa, tomatoes with chilis, black beans, half of the can of sweet corn, verde enchilada sauce, cumin, chili powder, white pepper, black pepper, and salt to taste. Mix everything well, and then pour into the 8 x8 baking dish. Cover with the last cup of cheese and then bake in the oven for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and allow to cool for 5 minutes. Then top with chopped Roma tomato, chopped avocado, green onion tops, and remaining 2 tsp of cilantro. Serve immediately.", 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/cheesy-chicken-enchilada-quinoa-casserole/', 'cui': 'mexican', 'diets': ['gluten free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small Avocado (chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_16018', 'name': 'black beans', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 (15oz) can of black beans (I like the low sodium version)'}, {'iid': 's_10011693', 'name': 'canned tomatoes', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 (10oz) can of tomatoes with green chilis'}, {'iid': 's_2009', 'name': 'chili powder', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp chili powder'}, {'iid': 's_20137', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup cooked quinoa'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'cumin', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp cumin'}, {'iid': 's_6599', 'name': 'verde enchilada sauce', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 (10oz) can of verde enchilada sauce'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'cilantro', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': 'fresh cilantro (2Tbsp and 2 tsp separated)'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'green onion tops', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'green onion tops (chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_10211529', 'name': 'roma tomato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 Roma tomato (chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt to taste'}, {'iid': 's_1011026', 'name': 'cheese', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups of shredded cheese (my favorite is the Kraft Mexican 4 cheese blend and one bag equals two cups!)'}, {'iid': 's_1055062', 'name': 'chicken breast', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 boneless skinless chicken breast (boiled and shredded)'}, {'iid': 's_10111168', 'name': 'corn', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 (15oz) can of sweet corn (you are only going to use half of the can)'}, {'iid': 's_2032', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp white pepper'}]}, {'rid': 's_715957', 'title': 'Zesty Green Pea and Jalapeño Pesto Pasta', 'inst': 'Soak the sun-dried tomatoes in hot water for 20 to 30 minutes. Drain and chop.Cook the pasta in a large saucepan of boiling salted water according to package directions. Two minutes before the pasta is finished cooking, toss in the remaining peas.In a small food processor, process the sun-dried tomatoes, 1/4 cup of the peas, basil, mint, shallot or onion, garlic, jalapeo, lemon juice and zest, salt and pepper with 3 tablespoons of olive oil in a small food processor. Process until smooth. Add another tablespoon of olive oil if the pesto is too thick to process. Drain the pasta and peas and toss with the pesto. Serve hot or warm, or cold as a salad.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodandspice.com/2014/09/zesty-green-pea-and-jalapeno-pesto-pasta.html', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'fresh basil leaves', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup fresh basil leaves'}, {'iid': 's_2064', 'name': 'fresh mint leaves', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '3/4 cup fresh mint leaves'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11979', 'name': 'jalapeno', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 jalapeño, seeded and chopped'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'juice and zest from 1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11304', 'name': 'peas', 'qty': 1.25, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/4 cups fresh garden peas or defrosted frozen green peas'}, {'iid': 's_11320420', 'name': 'rotini pasta', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '3 cups dried fusilli or rotini pasta'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of sea salt'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'red onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 shallot or small red onion, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11955', 'name': 'sun-dried tomatoes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 sun-dried tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'ground', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon fresh ground black, green or white pepper'}]}, {'rid': 's_648320', 'title': 'Jade Buddha Salmon Tartare', 'inst': 'Combine all ingredients except lime juice and vinegar. Chill for 30 minutes. Add lime juice and vinegar, adjust to perfect, and serve.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/7J3VXBX3/jade-buddha-salmon-tartare', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'primal', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_15076', 'name': 'salmon', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '12 ounces salmon, finely diced'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'green onion', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons chopped green onion'}, {'iid': 's_11156', 'name': 'chives', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon chopped chives'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'cilantro', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon cilantro'}, {'iid': 's_1012044', 'name': 'thai basil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon thai basil'}, {'iid': 's_11216', 'name': 'ginger', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons grated ginger'}, {'iid': 's_1009159', 'name': 'lime zest', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'zest of 1 lime'}, {'iid': 's_9160', 'name': 'lime juice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': 'good tablespoon of lime juice'}, {'iid': 's_1022053', 'name': 'rice vinegar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon champagne or rice vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_10011819', 'name': 'habanero sauce and chile', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'habanero sauce and minced green chile'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil to coat', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'olive oil to coat'}]}, {'rid': 's_716432', 'title': 'Finger Foods: Frittata Muffins', 'inst': '', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://fullbellysisters.blogspot.com/2014/05/finger-foods-frittata-muffins.html', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'ketogenic'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11090', 'name': 'broccoli', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '3/4 cup chopped, cooked broccoli'}, {'iid': 's_11156', 'name': 'chives', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '2 T chopped chives'}, {'iid': 's_1011077', 'name': 't cream', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 + 2 T cream or whole milk'}, {'iid': 's_1123', 'name': 'eggs', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 eggs'}, {'iid': 's_10011821', 'name': 'orange pepper', 'qty': 0.33333334, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/3 cup minced orange pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'serving', 'raw': 'salt and pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1001009', 'name': 'cheddar cheese', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomato', 'qty': 0.33333334, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/3 cup seeded, chopped tomato'}]}, {'rid': 's_798400', 'title': 'Spicy Black-Eyed Pea Curry with Swiss Chard and Roasted Eggplant', 'inst': 'Rinse the black-eyed peas and soak in several inches of water for 6 hours or overnight. Drain and rinse, then transfer to a large saucepan and cover with fresh water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer for 40 to 60 minutes. Take care not to overcook  the beans should be tender but not be falling apart. Drain and set aside.To prepare the eggplant, cut of the stem and bottom edge and then cut in half lengthwise. Score the flesh into diagonal 1-inch lines, then turn and score again until you have a diagonal pattern. Take care not to cut through the skin. Sprinkle with some salt and let sit for 40 minutes. Rinse and squeeze out any excess water. Brush the eggplant with some oil and transfer to a roasting pan. Bake in a preheated 400 oven until the flesh appears collapsed and is wrinkly. Remove from heat and let cool for about 10 minutes, season with a bit of salt, and remove the flesh from the eggplant. If there is too much water, drain in a strainer. Set aside. Heat the oil over medium heat in the same saucepan used to cook the black-eyed peas. When hot, toss in the shallots and chilies and saut for 2 to 3 minutes. Now add the spices and stir for another minute, until fragrant. Add the tomato, cook for another few minutes, and then add the eggplant and black-eyed peas, and cook for another few minutes, stirring often. Pour a few tablespoons of water into the pan and add handfuls of chard at a time until wilted. Add more water as necessary. Add the lemon juice and salt to taste near the end of the cooking time. Remove from heat, cover, and let sit for a few minutes before serving.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodandspice.com/2016/08/spicy-black-eyed-pea-curry-with-swiss.html', 'cui': 'indian', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_16063', 'name': 'black-eyed peas', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2/3 cup dried black-eyed peas (2 cups cooked)'}, {'iid': 's_2015', 'name': 'curry powder', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons curry powder'}, {'iid': 's_93663', 'name': 'garam masala', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon garam masala'}, {'iid': 's_11209', 'name': 'globe', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large globe or Italian eggplant'}, {'iid': 's_1002013', 'name': 'ground coriander', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon ground coriander'}, {'iid': 's_1012014', 'name': 'ground cumin', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon ground cumin'}, {'iid': 's_1002024', 'name': 'ground mustard powder', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon ground mustard powder'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'juice from 1 lemon (3 tablespoons)'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_31015', 'name': 'chilies', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 green or red chilies, seeded and finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon sea salt, or to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11677', 'name': 'shallots', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 shallots, mined'}, {'iid': 's_11147', 'name': 'swiss chard', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch Swiss chard, trimmed and chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium tomato, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '5 tablespoons water, or more as needed'}]}, {'rid': 's_652417', 'title': 'Moroccan chickpea and lentil stew', 'inst': 'Heat oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat, add onion and cook for about 3 minutes. Add celery, carrot and broccoli to pan and saut for about 5 minutes. Add in all seasonings and cook additional 1 minute. Add water, tomato paste, chickpeas and lentils, bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat to low and simmer for 20 minutes.Meanwhile, cook couscous in separate pan according to package directions. Add cilantro and lemon juice to stew and serve over warm couscous.', 'serv': 3, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/C6DXLHJH/moroccan-chickpea-and-lentil-stew', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11090', 'name': 'broccoli', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup broccoli'}, {'iid': 's_16058', 'name': 'chickpeas', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'can', 'raw': '1 can chickpeas, rinsed and drained'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '2 large carrots, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10111143', 'name': 'celery stalks', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 celery stalks, chopped ili 1/3 cup chopped celery root'}, {'iid': 's_16070', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup cooked lentils'}, {'iid': 's_20028', 'name': 'couscous', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup couscous'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'cilantro', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Fresh cilantro, optional'}, {'iid': 's_1012010', 'name': 'ground cinnamon', 'qty': 0.125, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '⅛ tsp ground cinnamon'}, {'iid': 's_1012014', 'name': 'ground cumin', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp ground cumin'}, {'iid': 's_2043', 'name': 'ground turmeric', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp ground turmeric'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1 Tbs lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_2028', 'name': 'paprika', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp paprika'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11887', 'name': 'tomato paste', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '2-3 Tbs tomato paste'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 ½ cups water'}]}, {'rid': 's_661925', 'title': 'Strawberry-Mango Quinoa Salad', 'inst': 'Prepare the quinoa: In a medium saucepan combine the quinoa, water and 1/4 t. salt. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until the liquid is just absorbed, about 15 minutes. Spread the cooked quinoa out on a baking sheet to cool for about 20 minutes.In a large bowl whisk together lime juice, zest, honey, sour cream and olive oil. Add the cooled quinoa, strawberries, mango, cucumber and mint. Toss well to combine and season with salt &amp; pepper. Serve immediately.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/K2BYJP76/strawberry-mango-quinoa-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11206', 'name': 'cucumber', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '3/4 cup cucumber'}, {'iid': 's_2064', 'name': 'mint', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons chopped fresh mint'}, {'iid': 's_19296', 'name': 'honey', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '1 T. honey'}, {'iid': 's_9160', 'name': 'lime juice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '2 T. lime juice'}, {'iid': 's_1009159', 'name': 'lime zest', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '1/2 t. lime zest'}, {'iid': 's_9176', 'name': 'mango', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 mango'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '1/4 c. olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'pepper'}, {'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '1 c. quinoa, well rinsed'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt'}, {'iid': 's_1001116', 'name': 'cream', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '1 T. sour cream (or plain yogurt can be subbed)'}, {'iid': 's_9316', 'name': 'strawberries', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups strawberries, hulled and quartered'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '1 1/2 c. water'}]}, {'rid': 's_636787', 'title': 'Caldo Verde - Portuguese Kale Soup', 'inst': "Chop your onions, slice your carrots and smash your garlic. Set aside. Peel and chop the potatoes. Set aside in a bowl of cold water. Remove the casing from your chorizo. This is an important step. Chorizo casing is tough and unforgiving and will make the sausage link curl during the cooking process. Just remove it and don't worry about appearance. Cut the links length-wise then chop into half-moons. Sautee in a separate pan until the are nice and browned. Don't put into the pot until the last minute, otherwise the color of the chorizo will leach into the soup turning it a weird red color. Now it's time to prepare the kale. With each individual leaf, cut out the stem. You can do this several ways. Cut a triangle out of the leaf, or fold over the leaf and cut out the stem that way. Or rip off the halves of the leaves off the stem. I like a little bit of stem to give some crunch and texture. Tightly roll the leaf into a bundle. Run your knife over it to julienne the leaf into thin strips. Don't worry if it's not perfect. Set aside the kale. In a big pot, sautee your onions, carrots and garlic in a bit of olive oil. Once the vegetables start to soften, add the potatoes and some crushed red pepper flakes. Stir the pot and cook the potatoes until the outer edges start turning clear. Then add the 6 cups of water and 2 bouillion packets (or 4 cups of broth and 2 cups of water) to the pot. Bring to a boil then let simmer until the potatoes are cooked. With a wooden spoon, mash the potatoes against the side of the pot. Do this until almost all the chunks of potatoes are mashed. Leave some chunks behind. This will give your soup a wonderful hearty texture. Now it's time to add the Kale. It looks like a lot and will fill up your whole pot but not to worry because it wilts down pretty quickly. Cook for 5 minutes at a simmer then stir in chorizo sausage. Serve hot or at room temperature (the latter is my favorite). Eat with a nice crusty loaf of Portuguese bread. Enjoy!", 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/7SDK7CGK/caldo-verde-portuguese-kale-soup', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'whole 30'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1/2 large onion chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 carrots peeled and sliced'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 garlic cloves smashed'}, {'iid': 's_11352', 'name': 'potatoes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '4 large yellow potatoes chopped'}, {'iid': 's_99231', 'name': 'chorizo links', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 chorizo links with casings removed, halved and chopped'}, {'iid': 's_6172', 'name': 'chicken stock and 2 cups of water', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '4 cups of chicken stock and 2 cups of water'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'kale', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch of kale julienned'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'of water and 2 packets of chicken boullion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': 'cup or 6 of water and 2 packets of Chicken Boullion'}, {'iid': 's_1032009', 'name': 'pepper flakes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'crushed red pepper flakes'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper to taste'}]}, {'rid': 's_652423', 'title': 'Moroccan Couscous and Chickpea Salad', 'inst': 'Heat broth and a teaspoon of salt and bring to a boil. Place couscous in a bowl and add broth.  Cover bowl to let couscous absorb liquid.After  5 minutes, remove cover and fluff couscous with a fork.In a large bowl, add the chickpeas, pistachios, red peppers, green onions and parsley and mix well. Add the zest and juice of the lemon and mix again. Add the spice mixture over the couscous and mix well. Taste, and add salt if needed. Let the salad marinate for an hour or so before serving.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/CCZR4V77/moroccan-couscous-and-chickpea-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_16058', 'name': 'chickpeas', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'ounce', 'raw': '15 ounce can of chickpeas (garbanzo beans), rinsed and strained'}, {'iid': 's_2031', 'name': 'cayenne', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon cayenne'}, {'iid': 's_2010', 'name': 'cinnamon', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon cinnamon'}, {'iid': 's_20028', 'name': 'couscous', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups couscous'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'green onions', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 chopped green onions or scallions'}, {'iid': 's_2021', 'name': 'ground ginger', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon ground ginger'}, {'iid': 's_2025', 'name': 'ground nutmeg', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg'}, {'iid': 's_9150', 'name': 'lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup chopped parsley'}, {'iid': 's_12151', 'name': 'pistachio nuts', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup shelled and unsalted pistachio nuts'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small red pepper, diced'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt to taste'}, {'iid': 's_2043', 'name': 'turmeric', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon turmeric'}, {'iid': 's_6615', 'name': 'vegetable broth', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups vegetable broth'}]}, {'rid': 's_715447', 'title': 'Easy Vegetable Beef Soup', 'inst': 'To get started, bring 4 quarts of water to a boil in a large pot. While waiting on the water to boil, cut the beef short ribs into bite-sized pieces and add them to the water. Add in diced tomatoes, potatoes, diced onion, parsley, garlic powder, beef bouillon cubes, Italian seasoning, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, bay leaves, and stir. Then add carrots, celery, black-eyed peas, butter beans, corn, and macaroni. Heat on high, stirring occasionally until the stew mixture comes to a boil. Once you have reached a boil, cover with a lid, lower heat enough to keep it simmering.\xa0 Continue to simmer for 1.5 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.', 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/vegetable-beef-stew-recipe/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_13149', 'name': 'beef short ribs', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'lbs', 'raw': '3 lbs of boneless beef short ribs'}, {'iid': 's_10120499', 'name': 'elbow macaroni', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup uncooked elbow macaroni'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water 4 qts', 'qty': 16.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '16 cups of water 4 Qts'}, {'iid': 's_10011693', 'name': 'canned tomatoes', 'qty': 28.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 28oz can diced tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_11352', 'name': 'potatoes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of small diced potatoes'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'on carrots', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup on thin sliced carrots'}, {'iid': 's_11143', 'name': 'celery', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup thin sliced celery'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups chopped onion'}, {'iid': 's_11168', 'name': 'kernal corn', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 15oz kernal corn (uncooked)'}, {'iid': 's_10016073', 'name': 'butter beans', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 15oz can butter beans'}, {'iid': 's_10016063', 'name': 'eyed peas', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 15oz can black – eyed peas'}, {'iid': 's_2004', 'name': 'bay leaves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 bay leaves'}, {'iid': 's_1022020', 'name': 'garlic powder', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 Tbsp garlic powder'}, {'iid': 's_1052047', 'name': 'celery salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp celery salt'}, {'iid': 's_6971', 'name': 'worcestershire sauce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 Tbsp Worcestershire sauce'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 Tbsp salt'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 Tbsp fresh ground pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1022027', 'name': 'seasoning', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 Tbsp Italian seasoning'}, {'iid': 's_6076', 'name': 'beef bouillon cubes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 beef bouillon cubes'}, {'iid': 's_2029', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 Tbsp dried parsley or fresh parsley'}]}, {'rid': 's_716311', 'title': 'Mango Fried Rice', 'inst': 'Wash your rice and bring to boil on medium heat with very little water as you are still going to cook it in chicken stock.Once the rice is slightly soft and the initial water has dried up, reduce the heat and pour in the chicken stock and cook till the chicken stock is all absorbed and has dried up. The chicken stock if freshly made will have some oil from the chicken so your rice does not need oil.Increase the heat and stir in the chopped vegetables and pepper. Add your seasoning cube.Finally stir in your cubed mango and serve warm with any protein of your choice. I’d say chicken but it’s up to you.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.afrolems.com/2015/05/02/mango-fried-rice/', 'cui': 'chinese', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_6172', 'name': 'chicken stock', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups of chicken stock'}, {'iid': 's_99186', 'name': 'seasoning cubes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Seasoning cubes'}, {'iid': 's_9176', 'name': 'mango', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'slices', 'raw': '3 slices of mango cubed'}, {'iid': 's_20444', 'name': 'rice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of rice'}, {'iid': 's_11583', 'name': 'vegetables', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of chopped vegetables'}, {'iid': 's_10011819', 'name': 'scotch bonnet pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 scotch bonnet pepper'}]}, {'rid': 's_157344', 'title': 'Spicy Salad with Kidney Beans, Cheddar, and Nuts', 'inst': 'Rinse and drain the kidney beans, cut the sundried tomatoes, and tear the slice of cheese into small pieces. Put the mixed greens in a bowl and top with kidney beans, sundried tomatoes, cheddar cheese, and nuts. Mix together the olive oil, balsamic vinegar, and hot sauce in a small bowl. Pour the dressing over the salad. Fast, easy, and healthy-- one of my favorite lunches!', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'http://spoonacular.com/-1384191937003', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_12061', 'name': 'almonds', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'grams', 'raw': '15 grams almonds'}, {'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 avocado'}, {'iid': 's_2069', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'ml', 'raw': '5 ml balsamic vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_1009', 'name': 'cheddar cheese', 'qty': 30.0, 'unit': 'grams', 'raw': '1/4 cup (30 grams) cheddar cheese'}, {'iid': 's_16033', 'name': 'kidney beans', 'qty': 113.0, 'unit': 'grams', 'raw': '1/2 cup (113 grams) cooked kidney beans'}, {'iid': 's_21052', 'name': 'greens', 'qty': 150.0, 'unit': 'grams', 'raw': '150 grams mixed greens'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': 'ml', 'raw': '10 ml olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_12585', 'name': 'roasted cashews', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'grams', 'raw': '15 grams roasted salted cashews'}, {'iid': 's_11955', 'name': 'sundried tomatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2-3 sundried tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_1026168', 'name': 'tabasco', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'dashes', 'raw': '2 dashes (or more if you like it hot!) Tabasco'}]}, {'rid': 's_658509', 'title': 'Roasted Broccoli with Lemon and Garlic', 'inst': 'Preheat the oven to 400 degrees FIn a large bowl, add broccoli florets, olive oil, salt, pepper and garlic. Spread the broccoli out in an even layer on a baking sheet. Bake in the preheated oven until broccoli is tender enough to pierce the stems with a fork, 15 to 20 minutes. Remove and place in a bowl, toss with lemon juice.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/3Z8R4RGY/roasted-broccoli-with-lemon-and-garlic', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10011090', 'name': 'broccoli florets', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '5 cups Organic Broccoli Florets'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons Extra Virgin Olive Oil'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove of garlic, or more'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '½ teaspoons Ground Black Pepper'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '½ teaspoons Lemon Juice'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon salt'}]}, {'rid': 's_716195', 'title': 'Spicy Indian-Style Hummus', 'inst': 'Rinse the chickpeas and soak for 8 hours or overnight covered in several inches of water with a little yogurt whey or lemon juice added. Drain and rinse, then transfer to a large saucepan.  Cover with several inches of fresh water, bring to a boil, reduce the heat to medium-low and cover.  Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until the beans are buttery soft. Drain.In a food processor, combine all of the ingredients and process until you have a thick, smooth paste. You may need to add extra olive oil or a bit of water if you want a thinner paste. Makes 3 cups, nutrition information is based on 1/4 cup serving.', 'serv': 12, 'url': 'https://www.foodandspice.com/2012/07/spicy-hummus-indian-style.html', 'cui': 'middle eastern', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1032035', 'name': 'asafetida', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of asafetida'}, {'iid': 's_2031', 'name': 'cayenne', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon cayenne'}, {'iid': 's_16056', 'name': 'chickpeas', 'qty': 1.25, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/4 cups dried chickpeas'}, {'iid': 's_11156', 'name': 'chives', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup fresh chives, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10211216', 'name': 'ginger', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'inch', 'raw': '1-inch piece fresh ginger, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10511297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup fresh parsley or cilantro, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1002013', 'name': 'ground coriander', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon ground coriander'}, {'iid': 's_1012014', 'name': 'ground cumin', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon ground cumin'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'fresh ground black pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'juice from 1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 - 3 tablespoons olive oil (or more to achieve your desired consistency'}, {'iid': 's_11819', 'name': 'chilies', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 fresh green or red chilies, seeded and chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon sea salt, or to taste'}, {'iid': 's_12698', 'name': 'tahini', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup tahini'}, {'iid': 's_2043', 'name': 'turmeric', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon turmeric'}]}, {'rid': 's_716361', 'title': 'Stir Fried Quinoa, Brown Rice and Chicken Breast', 'inst': 'In a bowl, season the chicken breast with the seasoning cubes and suya spice and allow to marinate for 2 hours or if you are really hungry, you can use immediately.In a pot of boiling water (1 cup), pour in your quinoa mix and the teaspoon of oil and allow to boil till soft which should take about 5-7 minutes. Pour into a bowl and set aside.In a pan, heat up the melted butter and pan fry on medium heat the chicken breast, constantly flipping it over so it browns\xa0on both sides, reduce the heat, cover the pan and allow the chicken cook properly. If the pan becomes to dry, add 2 tablespoons of water.Stir in the chopped vegetables into the pan of frying chicken and finally add the quinoa/brown rice mix. Serve hot!', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.afrolems.com/2014/06/26/stir-fried-quinoa-brown-rice-and-chicken-breast/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1032027', 'name': 'suya spice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon of suya spice or Yaji (optional)'}, {'iid': 's_20040', 'name': 'quinoa and brown rice mix', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup of quinoa and brown rice mix'}, {'iid': 's_1001', 'name': 'butter', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1.5 teaspoon of melted butter'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'handful', 'raw': 'A handful of chopped carrots'}, {'iid': 's_10311529', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 whole cherry tomatoes (optional)'}, {'iid': 's_5062', 'name': 'chicken breast', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 chicken breast (Thinly sliced)'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves of garlic'}, {'iid': 's_99186', 'name': 'seasoning cubes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'serving', 'raw': 'Seasoning cubes'}, {'iid': 's_11333', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'handful', 'raw': 'A handful of chopped green pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10211529', 'name': 'roma tomato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium roma tomato'}, {'iid': 's_10011819', 'name': 'scotch bonnet pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 scotch bonnet pepper (ata rodo)'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'spring onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 chopped spring onion'}, {'iid': 's_4669', 'name': 'vegetable oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon of vegetable oil'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup water'}]}, {'rid': 's_765011', 'title': 'Snap Pea and Green Bean Salad with Arugula Pesto', 'inst': 'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.While your water is coming to a boil, prepare your arugula pesto and cilantro cream drizzle.In the bowl of your food processor, add the almonds, pistachios, garlic, lemon zest, baby arugula and basil leaves. Pulse 8-9 times until completely broken up. With the food processor running, slowly pour in the olive oil until the pesto just comes together. Season to taste with salt and black pepper and transfer to a large bowl.In the same food processor bowl (wipe clean if you wish), combine the yogurt and cilantro. Pulse until the two ingredients come together. Season to taste with salt and black pepper and set aside.Have an ice bath ready. Add the snap peas and beans to the boiling water and blanch for about 1 minute and 30 seconds. Drain and transfer immediately to the ice bath to cool down. Drain again once the veggies are cool, and pat them dry. Add the veggies to the bowl with the pesto and toss to coat. Pour the veggies onto a large platter and drizzle with the cilantro cream. Top with micro greens and sliced almonds. Enjoy immediately or place in the refrigerator to chill.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/snap-pea-green-bean-salad-arugula-pesto/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_12061', 'name': 'roasted almonds', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup roasted almonds'}, {'iid': 's_12061', 'name': 'almonds', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon slice almonds'}, {'iid': 's_10011959', 'name': 'baby arugula', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups baby arugula'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil leaves', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 basil leaves'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'cilantro', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup cilantro'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup extra virgin olive oil (more as needed)'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '3 cloves of garlic'}, {'iid': 's_21052', 'name': 'micro greens', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup micro greens or sprouts'}, {'iid': 's_9156', 'name': 'lemon zest', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'zest from 1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_12151', 'name': 'pistachios', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup shelled pistachios'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10011300', 'name': 'snap peas', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound snap peas'}, {'iid': 's_93711', 'name': 'wax beans', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound green or wax beans'}, {'iid': 's_1001116', 'name': 'yogurt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup plain yogurt or sour cream'}]}, {'rid': 's_660228', 'title': 'Skinny Kale Basil Pesto', 'inst': 'Remove the kale and basil leaves from the stem and rinse. Roughly chop the kale leaves so that they fit inside a food processor. Place the kale and basil leaves into a food processor and chop until the leaves turn into small pieces. Add the rest of the ingredients into the food processor and mix until everything is well blended. Pour out all the ingredients into a dish and enjoy with your favorite dishes!', 'serv': 3, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/6K5LNQ7F/skinny-kale-basil-pesto', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'kale leaves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups packed kale leaves'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil leaves', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1.5 cups packed basil leaves'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 small lemon, juiced'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 garlic cloves'}, {'iid': 's_16112', 'name': 'miso paste', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1 Tbs miso paste'}, {'iid': 's_1032', 'name': 'parmesan cheese', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '2 Tbs freshly grated parmesan cheese'}, {'iid': 's_10112155', 'name': 'walnuts', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1/2 Tbs chopped walnuts'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1 Tbs water'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1/2 Tbs olive oil'}]}, {'rid': 's_716408', 'title': 'Greek-Style Baked Fish: Fresh, Simple, and Delicious', 'inst': 'Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F. Choose an oven-proof baking dish that your fish will fit in without overlapping and spray it with cooking spray. Lay the fish fillets in the baking pan in a single layer, season with salt and pepper, then top the fish with red onion and bell pepper. Sprinkle with dried basil and oregano, the tomato, and the feta cheese, then drizzle the white wine and olive oil over top. Grind some fresh pepper over the top. Bake uncovered for about 12 – 15 minutes or until the fish flakes easily with a fork. Squeeze the lemon wedges over the cooked fish, garnish with the fresh basil and/or oregano and serve with hot cooked rice.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://fullbellysisters.blogspot.com/2012/04/greek-style-baked-fish-fresh-simple-and.html', 'cui': 'mediterranean', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 bell pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10220445', 'name': 'rice', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Cooked rice, for serving'}, {'iid': 's_2003', 'name': 'basil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp Dried basil'}, {'iid': 's_1019', 'name': 'feta cheese', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '2 – 3 oz. of crumbled feta cheese per pound of fish'}, {'iid': 's_10115261', 'name': 'fish fillets', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '1 lb fish fillets'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 Tablespoons olive oil per pound of fish'}, {'iid': 's_2027', 'name': 'oregano', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp dried oregano'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Freshly ground pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 Red onion'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt & pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt & pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 tomato'}, {'iid': 's_14106', 'name': 'white wine', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '¼ cup white wine'}]}, {'rid': 's_661340', 'title': 'Spinach Salad with Strawberry Vinaigrette', 'inst': 'Place everything on a plate!  :) Place all ingredient in a blender and process until smooth, about 30 seconds Makes 1 cup Calories per Tbsp.  3,  Fat:  .01,  Sodium:  10,  Potassium:  13,  Carbs:  1,  Fiber:  .01,  Sugar:  .03,  Protein:  .01', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/5HT32BN5/spinach-salad-with-strawberry-vinaigrette', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'primal'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10112061', 'name': 'almonds', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp. sliced almonds'}, {'iid': 's_2069', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup – balsamic vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_5114', 'name': 'chicken', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '2 oz of chicken – cooked'}, {'iid': 's_1032046', 'name': 'dijon mustard', 'qty': 1.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 1/4 tsp. dijon mustard'}, {'iid': 's_1019', 'name': 'feta cheese', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1/2 oz. feta cheese'}, {'iid': 's_1012049', 'name': 'thyme', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp. fresh thyme'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/4 tsp. ground pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11677', 'name': 'shallot', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 shallot – chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'spinach leaves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups fresh spinach leaves'}, {'iid': 's_9316', 'name': 'strawberries', 'qty': 0.6666667, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '2/3 cup strawberries - chopped'}, {'iid': 's_9316', 'name': 'strawberries', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 strawberries - sliced'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup water'}]}, {'rid': 's_659135', 'title': 'Salmon with roasted vegetables', 'inst': 'Season the salmon fillets with some salt, pepper and a pinch of paprika and keep aside. Preheat the oven to 200 C.  Roughly dice the potatoes, parsnips and carrots and add to a roasting tray. Drizzle over the olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Mix well and roast for 15 minutes. Add in the onion and roast for a further 10-15 minutes Place the salmon fillets and tomatoes between the veg. Drizzle the lemon juice and sprinkle over the rosemary and thyme. Season lightly with salt and pepper and roast for 10-15 minutes or until the salmon and veg is cooked through. Serve with some green salad.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/7TTSVX56/salmon-with-roasted-vegetables', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'whole 30', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11352', 'name': 'potato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 potato'}, {'iid': 's_11298', 'name': 'parsnip', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 parsnip'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrot', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 carrot'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 onion, sliced'}, {'iid': 's_10311529', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes', 'qty': 150.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '150 g cherry tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'salmon', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'fillet', 'raw': '2 salmon fillets'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_1042027', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt, pepper and paprika for seasoning'}, {'iid': 's_2063', 'name': 'rosemary and thyme', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp of fresh rosemary and thyme, chopped'}]}, {'rid': 's_639851', 'title': 'Cod with Tomato-Olive-Chorizo Sauce and Mashed Potatoes', 'inst': 'If frozen, thaw completely the cod fillets, and dry them with paper towels. season with salt and set aside.Peel and quarter the potatoes, and cook in lightly salted water until tender.Meanwhile, fry the pepper in olive oil for 3-4 minutes. Add cubed sausage, saut for another 2-3 minutes. Add the whole plum tomatoes,  halve them with a flat end of a wooden spoon.Stir in olives and parsley, cook the sauce gently for 2 minutes. Set aside. Drain the potatoes and season with parsley, olive oil and lemon juice. Use a hand masher to mix and mash. Leave in a warm place. Place the cod fillets into a hot oiled non-stick pan and cook over a high heat for 5 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Serve with mashed potatoes and sauce.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/GNSQNH5W/cod-with-tomatoes-olives-and-chorizo', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'whole 30'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1059195', 'name': 'olives', 'qty': 50.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '50g pitted black olives, halved'}, {'iid': 's_15015', 'name': 'cod fillets', 'qty': 500.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '500 g cod fillets, fresh or frozen'}, {'iid': 's_10511297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '4 Tbs fresh parsley, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10511297', 'name': 'parsley leaves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Fresh parsley leaves, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1 Tbs lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '1 Tbs olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '2 Tbs olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10411529', 'name': 'plum tomatoes', 'qty': 240.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '240g whole plum tomatoes, canned'}, {'iid': 's_11352', 'name': 'potatoes', 'qty': 300.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '300 g potatoes'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 100.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '100g fresh red pepper, trimmed, cut into small strips'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp salt'}, {'iid': 's_7916', 'name': 'a semi-smoked sausage', 'qty': 100.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '100g chorizo or a semi-smoked sausage, cubed'}]}, {'rid': 's_664547', 'title': 'Vegetable Dip', 'inst': 'In a medium bowl combine all ingredients (except raw vegetables for dipping). Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve as a dip for raw vegetables. Makes approximately 3 cups.', 'serv': 3, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/WMHFXKKF/vegetable-dip', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11463', 'name': 'spinach', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 package frozen chopped spinach, thawed & drained (10 oz)'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': 'cup fresh onion, minced'}, {'iid': 's_1117', 'name': 'lowfat yogurt', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups plain lowfat yogurt'}, {'iid': 's_11583', 'name': 'vegetables', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Assorted raw vegetables for dipping'}]}, {'rid': 's_633921', 'title': 'Balsamic & Honey Glazed Salmon with Lemony Asparagus', 'inst': 'In a small mixing bowl or blender, combine all of the ingredients for the balsamic marinade except for the lemon juice (balsamic vinegar, apple cider vinegar, 1 tbsp grapeseed oil, honey, dried dill, herbs de provence, salt and pepper). Whisk or blend until oil and vinegar are well incorporated and no longer separate. Place salmon fillet in a baking dish (I use a small casserole dish). Pour the marinade over the salmon and allow it to marinate for at least 15 minutes (or up to 24 hours covered in the refrigerator).  Turn your oven on high broil. Just before putting the salmon in the oven, drizzle the lemon juice over the fish. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes on the top rack or until salmon is glazed, browned and sizzling.While the salmon is baking, prepare the asparagus.  Wash the asparagus and cut off the bottom inch and a half of each stalk and discard. Spread the asparagus on in a large skillet. Drizzle the grapeseed oil over the asparagus and spread the oil on the asparagus with your hands so that all stalks are completely coated. Sprinkle asparagus with desired amount of salt and pepper. Saute over medium heat for 5 minutes. Add the two tablespoons of vegetable stock and cover the skillet. Saute 4 minutes. Remove lid and add the minced garlic. Place cover back over the asparagus. Continue cooking an additional 3 to 5 minutes until asparagus is cooked but not too soft.  Grate lemon zest over the top of the asparagus.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/CK5NCLGT/balsamic-honey-glazed-salmon-with-lemony-asparagus', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2048', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons apple cider vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_11011', 'name': 'asparagus', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'stalks', 'raw': '12 stalks asparagus'}, {'iid': 's_2069', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_2017', 'name': 'dill', 'qty': 0.125, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '2 pinches (1/8 teaspoon) dried dill'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '3 cloves garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_4517', 'name': 'grapeseed oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon grapeseed oil'}, {'iid': 's_1012042', 'name': 'herbs de provence', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon herbs de Provence'}, {'iid': 's_19296', 'name': 'honey', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon honey'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'Juice of half a lemon'}, {'iid': 's_9156', 'name': 'lemon zest', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'Zest of 1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'salmon fillet', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '0.5 pound salmon fillet'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper'}, {'iid': 's_6615', 'name': 'vegetable stock', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons vegetable stock'}]}, {'rid': 's_641057', 'title': 'Curried Butternut Squash and Apple Soup', 'inst': 'Get ready two small saucepans. In one have together 1/2 of the squash and 1/2 of the apple  bring to a simmer, and simmer until just tender when pierced with a fork. In the other, add in the rest of the vegetables along with 1 cup of water  bring this to a rolling boil, reduce to a simmer, and simmer until very very tender. When very tender, remove the vegetables from the heat, and blend these vegetables together (without draining) with the Braggs, spices, sriracha and the additional 1/2 cup water. Mix the blended part of the soup with the simmered squash and apples. Mix in the cubed tofu, gently re-heat and serve.', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/FKQCYKYR/curried-butternut-squash-and-apple-soup', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11135', 'name': 'cauliflower', 'qty': 3.5, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 cup chopped cauliflower (3.5 oz)'}, {'iid': 's_11485', 'name': 'butternut squash', 'qty': 2.5, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1/2 cup chopped butternut squash (2.5 oz)'}, {'iid': 's_9003', 'name': 'apple', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1/2 cup peeled and chopped apple (2 oz)'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup water, plus about 1/2 cup extra'}, {'iid': 's_93767', 'name': 'braggs liquid aminos', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2-3 tsp Braggs liquid aminos'}, {'iid': 's_1022020', 'name': 'curry powder', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/2 heaping tsp: curry powder (or even 1 tsp, if you like the heat), garlic powder, onion powder'}, {'iid': 's_2021', 'name': 'ginger powder', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/4 tsp ginger powder'}, {'iid': 's_1016168', 'name': 'a squirt sriracha', 'qty': 0.125, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': 'a small squirt (1/8 tsp) sriracha'}, {'iid': 's_10016213', 'name': 'block lite tofu', 'qty': 0.125, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/8 block pressed lite firm tofu, cubed'}]}, {'rid': 's_632269', 'title': 'Amaranth and Roast Veggie Salad', 'inst': 'Cook the amaranth with about a cup of water until it reaches a sticky consistency Cut the onion roughly into chunks Add the onion and diced pumpkin to a tinfoil lined baking tray Drizzled over the olive oil and sprinkle with the herbal salt and pepper Put into a hot oven and roast until the edges of the pumpkin go crispy Just before the veggies are done, throw in the baby tomatoes Coat the veggies in the cooked amaranth Tear a few rocket leaves Toss together and there you have it, an unusual roast veggie salad! Serve warm', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/BPXZ2RCY/amaranth-and-roast-veggie-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_20001', 'name': 'amaranth', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup amaranth'}, {'iid': 's_1044053', 'name': 'basil-infused olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'basil-infused olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11422', 'name': 'pumpkin', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'packet', 'raw': '1/2 packet diced pumpkin'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 red onion'}, {'iid': 's_11959', 'name': 'rocket leaves', 'qty': 9.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'few rocket leaves'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'herbal salt', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'herbal salt'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'punnet baby tomatoes', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 punnet (basket) baby tomatoes'}]}, {'rid': 's_637162', 'title': 'Carrot and Cabbage Salad With Coriander+cumin Dry Rub', 'inst': 'Chop up the carrots and the cabbage into slivers of roughly the same size. Add the ground coriander, cumin seed, lime juice, and olive oil and massage it into the veggies. Add the fresh coriander and sunflower seeds on top.Leave aside for a couple of hours for the spices to seep into the veggies for added flavor.', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/MB7NYM87/carrot-and-cabbage-salad-with-coriandercumin-dry-rub', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'fodmap friendly', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups of carrots'}, {'iid': 's_2014', 'name': 'cumin seed powder', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/2 tsp cumin seed powder'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'coriander', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch of fresh coriander'}, {'iid': 's_11109', 'name': 'cabbage', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '3/4 cup green cabbage'}, {'iid': 's_1002013', 'name': 'ground coriander', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/2 tsp ground coriander'}, {'iid': 's_9160', 'name': 'juice of lime', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 Juice of lime'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon of olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11112', 'name': 'cabbage', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '3/4 cup red cabbage'}, {'iid': 's_12036', 'name': 'sunflower seeds', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons of sunflower seeds'}]}, {'rid': 's_982371', 'title': 'Instant Pot Quinoa Grain Bowl', 'inst': 'Rinse and drain the quinoa to remove the bitter and sometimes mildly soapy taste that can linger if not rinsed. Combine the quinoa, stock and seasonings in the Instant Pot together and then twist to lock the lid shut. Set the pot to Manual for 1 minute. At the end of the cook time, let the pot to natural pressure release for 10 minutes before carefully releasing the remaining pressure. Fluff the cooked quinoa with a fork. Now you have Instant Pot Quinoa! Add fruits and vegetables over a scoop of cooked quinoa and make an amazing quinoa grain bowl.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/instant-pot-quinoa-grain-bowl/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '½ ripe avocado sliced'}, {'iid': 's_11090', 'name': 'broccoli', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup chopped broccoli'}, {'iid': 's_10311529', 'name': 'rainbow cherry tomatoes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'fresh rainbow cherry tomatoes sliced'}, {'iid': 's_9433', 'name': 'clementine', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 clementine peeled'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'kale', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups of chopped kale'}, {'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups quinoa'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11001', 'name': 'baby brussell sprouts', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup baby brussell sprouts'}, {'iid': 's_1006615', 'name': 'stock', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups stock or broth'}]}, {'rid': 's_1095753', 'title': 'Roasted Cauliflower Detox Bowl with Tahini Sauce', 'inst': 'Soak the cashews overnight in water.Preheat the oven to 200C/~395 F. Chop the cauliflower into florets and toss with the olive oil and ground cumin. Roast for 20-25 minutes until golden.To make the sauce, add all ingredients except the water and salt to a food processor. While blending, drizzle in the water a little at a time until the sauce starts to become smooth. Continue processing, scraping down the sides or adding additional water as needed, until the sauce is as smooth as your food processor can make it. Add salt to taste.Boil the quinoa in a saucepan for 10 minutes then drain and set aside. Meanwhile, chop the kale and red cabbage into thin strips and saute in a frying pan with the minced garlic clove over a medium heat until wilted. Add in the quinoa and toss so everything is mixed together. Place some of the kale mixture in the bottom of a bowl and top with sliced avocado, some of the roasted cauliflower, a drizzle of the tahini sauce and if desired, sprinkle some cress on the top.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/6J6KLYH6/roasted-cauliflower-detox-bowl-with-tahini-sauce', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'kale leaves', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 Large Kale Leaves'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic'}, {'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup Quinoa'}, {'iid': 's_11112', 'name': 'cabbage', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/4 Red Cabbage'}, {'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 Avocado'}, {'iid': 's_11135', 'name': 'a cauliflower', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 a Large Cauliflower'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_1012014', 'name': 'ground cumin', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/4 tsp Ground Cumin'}, {'iid': 's_11203', 'name': 'garden cress', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'garden cress'}, {'iid': 's_10311215', 'name': 'garlic roasted', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'head', 'raw': '1 head garlic roasted'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'cashews soaked overnight in water', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup Raw Cashews soaked overnight in water'}, {'iid': 's_12698', 'name': 'tahini', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 tbsp Tahini'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '4-6 tbsp Water or more, as needed'}, {'iid': 's_1082047', 'name': 'kosher salt', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/4-1/2 tsp Kosher Salt'}]}, {'rid': 's_660405', 'title': 'Smoky Black Bean Soup With Sweet Potato & Kale', 'inst': 'Spread the dry beans out on a baking sheet and pick out any pebbles. Place the beans in a big soup pot, cover with water by 3 inches and allow them to soak overnight or for 6-8 hours, then discard that water. Return the soaked beans to the pot and cover with 3 inches of water again, bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium low, put the cover on and allow to cook until the beans start to get tender but still firm, about 1 1/2 hours. Drain the beans. Heat the oil in a soup pot over med-high heat. Add the onion along with a pinch of salt and saute until softened and golden. Stir in 1 tbsp of ground cumin, add the beans along with the broth or water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover and cook for 30 min. Meanwhile peel and chop the sweet potatoes. Wash the kale, remove the stems and chop the leaves. Remove half of the beans and liquid and set aside to cool a bit. Add the sweet potatoes and kale to the pot with some salt and pepper. Cover and cook for 10 minutes. Transfer the cooled beans to a blender and puree until smooth, then return them to the pot. Stir in the remaining 1 tbsp of ground cumin. Now add 1 tbsp of the chipotles in adobo. Taste and continue to add more until it has a spice level that you like. Adjust the salt &amp; pepper as needed. Serve with a dollop of sour cream.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/B8SQD87X/smoky-black-bean-soup-with-sweet-potato-kale', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_6194', 'name': 'chicken broth', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '6 cups Chicken Broth or Water'}, {'iid': 's_98839', 'name': 'chipotle chiles', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons Chipotle chiles'}, {'iid': 's_16014', 'name': 'black beans', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound Dried Black Beans'}, {'iid': 's_1012014', 'name': 'ground cumin', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons Ground Cumin'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'kale', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch kale'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 Onion – Chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt & pepper', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt & Pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11507', 'name': 'sweet potatoes', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'lbs', 'raw': '3 lbs sweet potatoes'}]}, {'rid': 's_715523', 'title': 'Chorizo and Beef Quinoa Stuffed Pepper', 'inst': 'The first thing you will want to do is heat the oven to 350, boil the water for the quinoa, and in a separate skillet brown the beef and chorizo together. Drain the meat mixture well, and then place into a medium mixing bowl.Once your quinoa is fully cooked, add it to the mixing bowl. Add the green onion tops, cumin, cayenne, chili powder, and monterrey jack and cheddar cheese. Mix well. Cut the tops from your bell peppers and scoop out any remaining seeds.Then take your meat mixture and start stuffing the bell peppers until they are full. Sprinkle with a little cheese and then bake in the oven for about 10 minutes until the bell pepper has softened. Serve immediately.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/chorizo-and-beef-quinoa-stuffed-pepper-recipe/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell peppers', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'bell peppers'}, {'iid': 's_2031', 'name': 'cayenne', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '½ tsp cayenne'}, {'iid': 's_2009', 'name': 'chili powder', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '¼ tsp chili powder'}, {'iid': 's_99233', 'name': 'chorizo', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound chorizo'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'cumin', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '¼ tsp cumin'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'green onion tops', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'green onion tops'}, {'iid': 's_1001025', 'name': 'monterrey jack and cheddar cheese', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '¼ cup mixed monterrey jack and cheddar cheese'}, {'iid': 's_23557', 'name': 'ground beef', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound lean ground beef'}, {'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup quinoa'}]}, {'rid': 's_632252', 'title': 'Alouette® Stuffed Mushroom Caps', 'inst': 'Preheat oven to 375 F. Place mushroom caps hollow side up on baking sheet. Fill each cap with 1 tsp. Alouette Garlic & Herbs Spreadable Cheese and sprinkle with seasoned bread crumbs. Bake 12-15 minutes. Garnish and serve.', 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/8LZ2BYQT/alouette-stuffed-mushroom-caps', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_18376', 'name': 'seasoned bread crumbs', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons seasoned bread crumbs'}, {'iid': 's_11238', 'name': 'mushroom caps', 'qty': 18.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '18 mushroom caps'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'alouette spinach & artichoke spread', 'qty': 6.5, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 package (6.5 oz.) Alouette Garlic & Herbs or Alouette Spinach & Artichoke Spread'}]}, {'rid': 's_639891', 'title': 'Coffee-braised Short Ribs', 'inst': 'Food Preheat oven to 300F. Heat oil in a large heavy stockpot over medium-high heat. Sprinkle short ribs with salt and pepper. Working in batches, add ribs to pot and cook until browned, about 4 minutes per side. Transfer to platter. Add onion, red bell pepper, and jalapeo to drippings in stockpot. Reduce heat to medium, cover, and cook until onion is tender, stirring occasionally, about 6 minutes.Stir in garlic and saut uncovered 1 minute. Add brown sugar, ancho chile powder, oregano, and cumin; stir 15 seconds. Stir in coffee, tomatoes with juice, and tomato paste. Bring to boil, scraping up browned bits. Return ribs and any juices to pot; bring to boil.Cover and bake until meat is very tender, about 1 hour 45 minutes. Spoon fat from surface of sauce. Season sauce to taste with salt and pepper. Transfer ribs to a platter and spoon sauce over top. Sprinkle with chopped cilantro.', 'serv': 5, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/8ZDDXLKG/coffee-braised-short-ribs', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1022009', 'name': 'ancho chile powder', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '1 1/2 tablespoons ancho chile powder'}, {'iid': 's_11531', 'name': 'canned tomatoes', 'qty': 14.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '14 -s 1/2 ounce can diced tomatoes in juice'}, {'iid': 's_10019334', 'name': 'brown sugar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons dark brown sugar'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'cilantro', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Chopped fresh cilantro'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 garlic cloves, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1012014', 'name': 'ground cumin', 'qty': 1.25, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '1 1/4 teaspoons ground cumin'}, {'iid': 's_11979', 'name': 'jalapeño', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large jalapeño, seeded and finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_2027', 'name': 'oregano', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons dried oregano'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large red bell pepper, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10013149', 'name': 'short', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '5 pounds short ribs'}, {'iid': 's_14209', 'name': 'strong freshly coffee', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups strong freshly brewed coffee'}, {'iid': 's_11887', 'name': 'tomato paste', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon tomato paste'}, {'iid': 's_10511282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large yellow onion, chopped'}]}, {'rid': 's_646651', 'title': 'Herb chicken with sweet potato mash and sautéed broccoli', 'inst': 'Preheat the oven to 350F (180C) or 320F (160C) for convection oven and cook the chicken according to the pack instructions. About 15 minutes before the end of the chicken cooking time, place the diced potato into boiling water for 5 minutes, then add the sweet potato and cook until the potatoes are tender. Roughly mash, adding butter, salt, and pepper to taste, then mash thoroughly. Heat the oil in a pan and quickly saut the broccoli until tender. Cover to keep warm. Remove the chicken from the oven, leave to cool for a minute then cut the bag open and gently tip the contents into a dish. Slice the chicken breasts into chunky pieces on a board, keeping the chicken breast shape together. Serve the mash potato topped with the chicken and remaining sauce with a side of broccoli.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/NHZKT2K8/serve-a-sensationally-seasoned-chicken-dish', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11090', 'name': 'broccoli', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium head', 'raw': '1 medium head of broccoli, cut into florets'}, {'iid': 's_1002044', 'name': 'pack maggi so herbs', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': '1 x pack Maggi So Juicy Mixed Herbs'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 60.0, 'unit': 'ml', 'raw': '1/4 cup olive oil (60 mL)'}, {'iid': 's_11353', 'name': 'russet potato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large Russet potato, peeled and diced'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper and salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Freshly ground black pepper and salt'}, {'iid': 's_1055062', 'name': 'chicken breasts', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '1 1/2 pounds of boneless, skinless chicken breasts'}, {'iid': 's_11507', 'name': 'sweet potatoes', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '3 large sweet potatoes, peeled and diced'}, {'iid': 's_1145', 'name': 'butter', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons Chilled unsalted butter'}]}, {'rid': 's_716330', 'title': 'Chicken and Mango Skewer', 'inst': 'Chop chicken breast into cubes and place on sticks. Set fire to your grill or oven. Place the chicken breast on the grill to heat up a little Mix all your seasoning in a bowl with your vegetable oil.With a brush, smear the mix on the chicken breast on both sides.Flip occasionally as it browns till its cooked. Stack your mangoes after the chicken is done but if your mangoes are firm, you can grill them as well. Serve on its own as an appetizer or with rice.', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.afrolems.com/2013/03/29/easter-special-chicken-and-mango-skewer/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'whole 30'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_5062', 'name': 'chicken breast', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1/4 pound of Skinless Chicken Breast'}, {'iid': 's_6080', 'name': 'chicken stock cube', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 chicken stock cube'}, {'iid': 's_9176', 'name': 'mangos', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '2 medium Mangos (Or canned mango slices)'}, {'iid': 's_1032009', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon Dry pepper (Chili flakes)'}, {'iid': 's_1032027', 'name': 'suya seasoning mix', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1.5 Tablespoon Suya seasoning mix'}, {'iid': 's_4669', 'name': 'cooking spoon of vegetable oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 cooking spoon of vegetable oil'}]}, {'rid': 's_640318', 'title': 'Crab Salad Stuffed Pita Pockets', 'inst': 'Mix crabmeat, apple and bell pepper together in a bowl.Season to taste, add coriander and fold mayonnaise through.Toast pita breads until puffed up, then cut open on one side.Stuff with some watercress, then the crab mixture. Serve immediately.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/4NJDB7X2/crab-salad-stuffed-pita-pockets', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9003', 'name': 'apple', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1/2 small apple, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_15141', 'name': 'crabmeat', 'qty': 300.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '2 150g cans white crabmeat'}, {'iid': 's_2012', 'name': 'coriander leaves', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup finely chopped coriander leaves'}, {'iid': 's_4641', 'name': 'mayonnaise', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons light mayonnaise'}, {'iid': 's_18413', 'name': 'wholewheat pita breads', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 wholewheat pita breads'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt & pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt & pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11591', 'name': 'watercress', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'handfuls', 'raw': '2 handfuls watercress'}, {'iid': 's_11951', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1/4 medium yellow bell pepper, finely chopped'}]}, {'rid': 's_642085', 'title': 'Easy Roasted Vegetables', 'inst': 'Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius (fan: 180 degrees Celsius) Peel and cut the vegetables into bite size pieces (the potatoes dont necessarily need to be peeled). Mix the olive oil, paprika, dried basil, salt and pepper in a large bowl before adding the vegetables. Mix everything together well. Place the vegetables on a large baking tray/baking dish. Make sure they are spread out evenly. Aim for single layer. Cook the vegetables in the oven for about 30 minutes. They should be tender but still have a slight bite to them.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/RFJQ5QGF/easy-roasted-vegetables', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11485', 'name': 'butternut squash', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 butternut squash'}, {'iid': 's_11080', 'name': 'beet roots', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 beet roots'}, {'iid': 's_11352', 'name': 'potatoes', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 potatoes'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_2028', 'name': 'paprika', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 tbsp paprika'}, {'iid': 's_2003', 'name': 'basil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 tbsp dried basil'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt & pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt & pepper'}]}, {'rid': 's_716437', 'title': 'Chilled Cucumber Avocado Soup with Yogurt and Kefir', 'inst': '', 'serv': 3, 'url': 'https://fullbellysisters.blogspot.com/2012/06/chilled-cucumber-avocado-soup-with.html', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 avocado'}, {'iid': 's_11206', 'name': 'persian cucumbers', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '5-6 persian cucumbers'}, {'iid': 's_9132', 'name': 'grapes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small handful', 'raw': 'small handful of grapes'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'juice of 1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_1230', 'name': 'kefir', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup plain kefir (can substitute buttermilk)'}, {'iid': 's_1001256', 'name': 'greek yogurt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup plain Greek yogurt'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup chopped red onion'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper, to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'scallions', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 scallions'}]}, {'rid': 's_664090', 'title': 'Turkish Chicken Salad with Home-made Cacik Yogurt Sauce', 'inst': 'First prepare the Cacik: For the Cacik: Chop the cucumber into tiny pieces, as small as you can, and place in a bowl. Cover the cucumber with salt and set aside for 30 minutes. The cucumbers will start to exude their juices which will flavour the yogurt nicely. Put a griddle pan on medium  high heat, cover the peppers with olive oil and start to char. Cut the tomato and cucumber into medium pieces. Slice the red onion as thin as you can. Chop the parsley fine. Place all ingredients in a bowl and cover with a the juice of 1 lemon. Season with salt and pepper. Let it sit in the fridge for 30 minutes  1 hour, stirring a couple times, so it starts to exude juice. Tear the lettuce into mouth-siazed peices. Cut the red cabbage into thin slices. Grate the carrot. Mix together in a bowl. Tear the chicken into large pieces and add to the salad. Remove the tomato salsa from the fridge. Drain the juice and keep for later. Now add the tomato, cucumber, parsley onion mix to the chicken salad, as well as the sliced gherkin. Lay out the salad on a large plate or chopping board. Serve with the charred peppers, cacik, salsa vinaigrette and some chilli sauce.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/XYFWSH25/a-turkish-inspired-chicken-salad-with-tomato-cucumber-red-onion-salsa-charred-green-peppers-and-home-made-cacik-delicious-and-healthy', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrot', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 carrot, grated'}, {'iid': 's_11206', 'name': 'cucumber', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 cucumber'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'small pieces', 'raw': '3 small pieces garlic'}, {'iid': 's_11941', 'name': 'pickled cucumbers / gherkins', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '2 large pickled cucumbers / gherkins, sliced'}, {'iid': 's_11979', 'name': 'jalapeno peppers', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '2 – 2 large Jalapeno peppers'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'Juice of 1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_10211205', 'name': 'lebanese cucumber', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small lebanese cucumber (or 1/3 of a large one)'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_11252', 'name': 'i gem lettuce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large head', 'raw': 'I large head green gem lettuce'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'handful', 'raw': 'Handful chopped parsley'}, {'iid': 's_11112', 'name': 'cabbage', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/4 red cabbage, thinly sliced'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small red onion'}, {'iid': 's_5114', 'name': 'roast chicken', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 whole roast chicken'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt & pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt & pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_1116', 'name': 'yoghurt', 'qty': 250.0, 'unit': 'ml', 'raw': '250ml plain Turkish or Greek-style yoghurt'}]}, {'rid': 's_636602', 'title': 'Butternut Squash Soup (In Half An Hour!)', 'inst': 'In large pot, saute onion in butter, ghee or olive oil until soft Add cubed squash and saute for a couple of minutes Add vegetable stock and 1 3 inch piece of kombu and bring to a boil Reduce heat and simmer until squash is soft (about 15 minutes)Using a slotted spoon, remove squash and puree in blender Return squash to pot and stir in black-eyed peas and cooked quinoa. Add greens for about five minutes until soft Add nutmeg, sea salt and pepper to taste', 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/24DYGNYL/butternut-squash-soup-in-half-an-hour', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11485', 'name': 'butternut squash', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 butternut squash, peeled, seeded and cut into small cubes'}, {'iid': 's_10016063', 'name': 'black-eyed peas', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'can', 'raw': '1 can black-eyed peas'}, {'iid': 's_11161', 'name': 'collard greens', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Collard greens (my choice), kale, spinach, beet greens, etc. cut into small pieces'}, {'iid': 's_20137', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Leftover cooked quinoa'}, {'iid': 's_11445', 'name': 'kombu', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'piece', 'raw': '1 piece of kombu'}, {'iid': 's_2025', 'name': 'nutmeg', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Nutmeg'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '2 T butter, ghee, or olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper'}, {'iid': 's_6615', 'name': 'vegetable broth', 'qty': 32.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 32 oz. organic vegetable broth (I like the Pacifica brand for its lack of unnecessary ingredients)'}, {'iid': 's_10511282', 'name': 'onions', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1-2 small yellow onions, cut up'}]}, {'rid': 's_716276', 'title': 'Doughnuts', 'inst': 'In a bowl mix the water with the yeast and honey, whisk and allow to sit for 15 minutes or until the mixture is foamy. Mix the flour with the salt and powdered milk and pour the yeast mixture into the bowl.Knead the dough till its elastic and not sticky and cover and leave to double in size. This could take 1-2 hours.On a lightly floured surface, roll out your dough but not to thin so your doughnuts are not flat and cut the dough into circles. If You have a doughnut cutter use that, if not use a small round shaped cover or bowl to make your circles and a smaller container for the middle hole. You can improvise and use the mouth of a plastic bottle to make the hole in the middle.Leave to rise for another 45 minutes. Heat up your oil and fry the doughnuts till they are brown on both sides.Vanilla Glaze Mix 1 cup of powdered sugar with 30 ml of milk and 1 teaspoon of vanilla. Whisk till its properly mixed and drizzle the doughnuts with it. Add sprinkles for garnishing Chocolate GlazeI used a chocolate sauce and drizzled over the doughnuts with sprinkles to top it.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.afrolems.com/2014/03/25/doughnuts-recipe/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_20081', 'name': 'flour', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1.5 cups of flour'}, {'iid': 's_19296', 'name': 'honey', 'qty': 30.0, 'unit': 'ml', 'raw': '30 ml honey'}, {'iid': 's_1090', 'name': 'powdered milk', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon of powdered milk'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'warm water', 'qty': 150.0, 'unit': 'ml', 'raw': '150 ml warm water'}, {'iid': 's_18375', 'name': 'yeast', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon yeast'}]}, {'rid': 's_1044252', 'title': 'Shredded Roast Beef Stuffed Sweet Potatoes (Whole 30 & PALEO)', 'inst': 'Place the roast in Crock Pot, cover with beef broth,  and cook on low for 8 hours. Fully cook the sweet potatoes when ready. When roast is finished, shred and serve over the sweet potatoes.', 'serv': 5, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/shredded-roast-beef-stuffed-sweet-potatoes/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'primal', 'whole 30'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_6008', 'name': 'beef broth', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'beef broth'}, {'iid': 's_23612', 'name': 'pot roast', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '2 lb roast'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_11507', 'name': 'sweet potatoes', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 sweet potatoes'}]}, {'rid': 's_649944', 'title': 'Lentil Mango Salad', 'inst': 'Clean and chop the onion, red pepper, garlic, Cilantro Peel and chop mango Place all salad ingredients in a bowl, add the oil, vinegar, season with salt and pepper Mix well and leave in the refrigerator for 1 / 2 hour This salad is left to eat alone or to accompany meat and poultry dishes, enjoy ...', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/TTBNDB7Q/lentill-mango-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'cilantro', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch Cilantro'}, {'iid': 's_16070', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound cooked lentils'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic'}, {'iid': 's_9176', 'name': 'mango', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 mango'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 red bell pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 red onion'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt'}, {'iid': 's_1002068', 'name': 'white wine vinegar', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup white wine vinegar'}]}, {'rid': 's_646043', 'title': 'Gujarati Dry Mung Bean Curry', 'inst': 'Wash the mung beans and boil them in plenty of hot water with a pinch of baking powder until al-dente. If you have a pressure cooker thats about 6-7 whistles. Drain and set aside.In a large pan heat the oil and add the mustard seeds (wait for them to pop) then add the cumin seeds, asafoetida, curry leaves, garlic and chillies. Saut until aromatic. Obviously dont let it burn. Add the tomatoes, turmeric and mung beans and cook for two minutes. Be careful not to mash it up as you stir. Add the salt, sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon powder and cook for a further two minutes.Throw in the chopped coriander, combine and serve.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/G6ZJW56S/gujarati-dry-mung-bean-curry', 'cui': 'indian', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_18369', 'name': 'baking powder', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small pinch', 'raw': '1 small pinch baking powder'}, {'iid': 's_11819', 'name': 'chillies', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '2 mediums hot chillies, minced'}, {'iid': 's_1012010', 'name': 'cinnamon powder', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon cinnamon powder'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'coriander', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup chopped coriander'}, {'iid': 's_2014', 'name': 'cumin seeds', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '2 teaspoons cumin seeds'}, {'iid': 's_93604', 'name': 'curry leaves', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 curry leaves'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice or', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon lemon juice or to taste'}, {'iid': 's_16080', 'name': 'mung beans', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups mung beans'}, {'iid': 's_2024', 'name': 'mustard seeds', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon mustard seeds'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt to taste'}, {'iid': 's_19335', 'name': 'sugar', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Sugar to taste'}, {'iid': 's_4584', 'name': 'sunflower oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon sunflower oil'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium tomato, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_2043', 'name': 'turmeric', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon turmeric'}]}, {'rid': 's_634437', 'title': 'Basil Tagliatelle with Roasted Red Bell Pepper Salad', 'inst': 'Go to my blog for the full instructions: http://gourmandelle.com/basil-tagliatelle-with-roasted-red-bell-pepper-salad/', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/B6VWDFWJ/basil-tagliatelle-with-roasted-red-bell-pepper-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10220409', 'name': 'tagliatelle', 'qty': 7.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '200g ( - 7 ounces) whole wheat tagliatelle'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell peppers', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '10 red bell peppers, medium'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 garlic cloves, minced'}, {'iid': 's_11297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '4 tbsp chopped parsley'}, {'iid': 's_1002055', 'name': 'horseradish', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '4 tbsp grated horseradish'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'green onions', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 green onions, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '4 tbsp lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '3 tbsp extra virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp sea salt'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 0.33333334, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/3 tsp ground pepper'}]}, {'rid': 's_655235', 'title': 'Peanut Butter and Jelly Smoothie', 'inst': 'Place ingredients in a high speed blender like Blendtec for super smooth texture, blend on high.If using a regular blender put milk and strawberries in then blend.Next, add banana pieces and peanut butter, process until smooth. Garnish with crushed peanuts and serve.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/K5KVRWVR/peanut-butter-and-jelly-smoothie', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'fodmap friendly'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10016223', 'name': 'almond milk', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup almond milk or other non-dairy milk (see my almond milk recipe)'}, {'iid': 's_9040', 'name': 'bananas', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 bananas, smashed (I used frozen)'}, {'iid': 's_16098', 'name': 'peanut butter', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup peanut butter'}, {'iid': 's_10819297', 'name': 'strawberries', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup strawberries (about 3 strawberries) or 1 Tbsp strawberry jam'}]}, {'rid': 's_652393', 'title': 'Moosewood Lentil Soup', 'inst': 'Place lentils and water in a soup pot or Dutch oven.Bring to a boil, lower heat to a simmer, and let cook until lentils are mushy (about 45 minutes). Add more water as needed, until the soup is your favorite consistency. Heat oil or melt butter in a medium-sized skillet. Add onion, celery, and carrots, and saut over medium heat for about 10 minutes. Add garlic, salt, pepper, and herbs of your choice, and saut about 5 minutes longer. Transfer to lentils.Stir in wine, if desired, lemon juice and molasses or brown sugar.Taste to correct seasonings, then simmer for At least 15 minutes longer. Serve hot, with a little vinegar drizzled onto each serving, and a sprinkling of minced Scallions or parsley on top, if desired.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/TNZ67L5Y/moosewood-lentil-soup', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Freshly-ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_19334', 'name': 'brown sugar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon molasses or brown sugar'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup chopped carrots'}, {'iid': 's_11143', 'name': 'celery', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup minced celery'}, {'iid': 's_1022042', 'name': 'herbs', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'pinches', 'raw': '3 pinches of dried herbs (thyme, oregano, or basil)'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic, chopped,'}, {'iid': 's_4517', 'name': 'grapeseed oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon grapeseed oil or butter'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons fresh lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_10316069', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '3 cups lentils, any type'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large onion, finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1022068', 'name': 'red wine vinegar', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Red wine vinegar for the top'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': 'medium ripe tomatoes, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup Boiling water'}]}, {'rid': 's_640828', 'title': 'Crispy Panko and Herb Crusted Salmon', 'inst': 'In a skillet heat 2-3 tablespoons of extra virgin olive oil. Add the chopped onions and leeks. Saute until translucent about 4 minutes. Add the chopped red peppers and tomatoes and continue cooking until soft. Set aside and allow to cool before adding to the panko breadcrumb mixture. Using a food processor, finely chop the parsley, garlic clove, and the lemon zest. Add the panko breadcrumbs,salt and pepper, pulse to blend. Transfer to a bowl and toss in the the onion, leek, tomato and red pepper mixture, which has been cooled. Blend in 3 tablespoons of extra virgin oil, enough to coat the bread mixture. Place the salmon flat side down on a cookie sheet, which has been lined with parchment paper. Spread the breadcrumb mixture on top of the fish to cover. Bake in a preheated 375F for 25- 35 minutes, depending on the thickness of the salmon fillet.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/THDLRSLW/crispy-panko-and-herb-crusted-salmon', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'salmon fillet', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '2 pound salmon fillet'}, {'iid': 's_11246', 'name': 'leek', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 leek finely chopped (white part of the leek)'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 red pepper diced'}, {'iid': 's_10311529', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 cherry tomatoes chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2-3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_10018079', 'name': 'panko crumbs', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 1/2 cup panko crumbs'}, {'iid': 's_10311297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup Italian parsley finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic clove', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 garlic clove finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_9156', 'name': 'lemon zest', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'zest of 1 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'dash', 'raw': 'dash of pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil'}]}, {'rid': 's_639411', 'title': 'Cilantro Lime Halibut', 'inst': 'Heat the oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Coat the filets with garlic pepper on the flesh side. When pan is heated, add filet flesh side down to pan to sear that side. Allow to cook for about 30 seconds. Then flip filets over with tongs. Add white wine to pan and cover to steam. After about 2 minutes, much of the wine will have evaporated. Add the chicken stock gradually. Allow the filets to steam for another couple of minutes. Then add the lime juice. When bubbling and both filets are opaque all the way through, add the green onions to the pan and swirl in the sauce for a moment. Remove filets to beds of lettuce. Add a tsp of the Blood Orange Olive, swirl the green onions in the sauce one more time and then pour equal parts over the fish. Garnish with fresh cilantro and lime wedges. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Serve immediately.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/W2C6K48J/cilantro-lime-halibut', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'primal', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_6172', 'name': 'chicken stock', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup chicken stock'}, {'iid': 's_11165', 'name': 'cilantro', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': 'A bunch of fresh cilantro'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'green onions', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 green onions, chopped from the white part halfway up the green part'}, {'iid': 's_15036', 'name': 'pacific halibut filets', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '2 (1/2 lb) Wild Pacific Halibut Filets'}, {'iid': 's_9160', 'name': 'juice of lime', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'juice of lime, divided'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'another slug of blood orange olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Another slug of Blood Orange Olive Oil'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': "mollie stone's blood orange olive oil", 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': "2 tsp Mollie Stone's Blood Orange Olive Oil (or regular olive oil)"}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'dusting of garlic-pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Dusting of garlic-pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_14106', 'name': 'white wine', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup white wine'}]}, {'rid': 's_636228', 'title': 'Broccoli Tartar', 'inst': 'Soak arame (seaweed can be found in a health-food store) in a bowl of pure water. Put the grill of the oven and put a pot of water on the fire with a pinch of sea salt.Wash the pepper, broccoli, parsley and tomatoes. Carve a cross down the tomatoes, halve the peppers and remove the seeds and cut the broccoli into chunks.When the water boils you immerse the tomatoes and leave them for a swim, get them and let them scare in cold water. They are now ready to go out of their jackets.Meanwhile, the broccoli  can be swimming for 6 minutes in the boiling water. Note: The water will cool off and when back to a boil, then add 5 minutes. Get them dry and cool under cold water, then they stay nice and green.The pepper may be under the grill until it sees black. Let them cool and peel them.Chop the parsley. Put the cooled broccoli in a long narrow bowl and blend finely with a hand blender. Add the oil and vinegar with the salt. Add half the parsley and mix into a smooth puree. If too grainy (dry) put some extra oil. Cut the unseeded, peeled tomatoes and peppers into very small pieces.The shallot or onion may be chopped in mini pieces. Add the chopped vegetables to the puree and stir gently with a spoon. The rest of the chopped parsley may be added now. A little salt, soy sauce and chili powder. Start with a little bit and add some more later if desired. The herbs de Provence can now embellish the whole with its bright flavor.The seaweed may now well out of the water and squeeze out any excess moisture. Cut the seaweed finely and mix carefully with the puree.With an ice cream spoon you  create beautiful balls and sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds.bon apptit', 'serv': 12, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/364Q5CSN/broccoli-tartar', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2048', 'name': 'apple vinegar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon of apple vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_11090', 'name': 'broccoli', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 broccoli'}, {'iid': 's_10011531', 'name': 'peeled/ tomatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 peeled/ seeded tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_10511297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'handfuls', 'raw': '2 handfuls finely chopped parsley'}, {'iid': 's_1012042', 'name': 'herbs de provence', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon large herbs de Provence'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11677', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 onion or 2 shallots'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 red bell pepper'}, {'iid': 's_2009', 'name': 'chili powder', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small pinch', 'raw': 'small pinch of red hot chili powder'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'sea salt to taste'}, {'iid': 's_12023', 'name': 'sesame seeds to decorate', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'toasted sesame seeds to decorate'}, {'iid': 's_16124', 'name': 'soy sauce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'dash', 'raw': 'dash of soy sauce'}, {'iid': 's_11583', 'name': 'colorful tartar on a bed of vegetables. also an touch', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Colorful tartar on a bed of raw green vegetables. Also an excellent touch for yo'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'a hand blender', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'A hand blender, griddle or grill'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'soaked arame', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup soaked arame (available in health food store)'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'hand blender', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'A hand blender, griddle or grill'}, {'iid': 's_-1', 'name': 'soaked arame', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup soaked arame (available in health food store)'}]}, {'rid': 's_661259', 'title': 'Spinach and Gorgonzola Stuffed Flank Steak', 'inst': 'Preheat oven to 37 Butterfly the steak by using a long sharp knife holding it parallel to the work surface, cut through the long side of the steak, stopping about  inch from the opposite side. If the steak is already thin, just pound it with a mallet to  inch thick. In a large skillet over medium heat add 1 tablespoon olive oil and saut` the shallots until soft, 2 minutes. Add the spinach and cook until just wilted, about 2 to 3 minutes. Transfer to a colander. When cool enough to handle, squeeze out all the moisture from the spinach and transfer to a medium bowl. Stir in the bread crumbs and cheese. Season with salt and pepper. Place the steak on a sheet of plastic wrap. Smear the spinach mixture evenly over the steak, leaving about 1 inch border along the side edge. Beginning with the side near you and using the plastic wrap as an aid, rollup the steak, gently pressing on the filling. Tie the rolled steak with twine at 2-3 inch interval. Season the outside with salt and pepper. Heat the remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil in a large ovenproof skillet over medium high heat. Sear the roast on all sided, about 2 minutes per side. Place in the oven and roast for 20 to 25 minutes. Transfer to a cutting board, tend with aluminum foil and allow resting for 10 minutes. To serve, remove the twine from the roast and cut into  inch to 1 inch thick slices.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/SWTFLZXM/spinach-and-gorgonzola-stuffed-flank-steak', 'cui': '', 'diets': [], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_23657', 'name': 'flank steak', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '1 1 ½ to 2 pounds flank steak trimmed'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '3 tablespoon olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11677', 'name': 'shallot', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 shallot finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'spinach', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '½ pound spinach, washed, stemmed and chopped'}, {'iid': 's_18079', 'name': 'bread crumbs', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '¾ cup fresh bread crumbs'}, {'iid': 's_1004', 'name': 'gorgonzola', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '¼ pound Gorgonzola or other blue cheese, crumbled'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper'}]}, {'rid': 's_664680', 'title': "Vegetarian Mushroom Shepherd's Pie", 'inst': "Peel potatoes and put them in a large pot filled with water. Boil them until they're tender. Mash them and let them cool for a while. Chop the mushrooms, carrot and red bell pepper. Add them into your food processor and pulse until all ingredients are well mixed together. Heat oil in a large skillet. Add the mixture above, diced onions, chopped dill and parsley, soy granules, eggs (or egg substitute) and spices. Saut for 10 minutes. * I added the soy granules without boiling them because the mushrooms contain a lot of water and these soy granules will absorb all excess water. Put some parchment paper on the bottom of a casserole. Divide the mashed potatoes in two. Place the first half in the casserole and spread it with a spatula. Add the filling. Place over the other half of mashed potatoes. Heat your oven at 39 Put the casserole in the oven. Cook for 40 minutes. Don't serve immediately. Let it cool for at least half an hour.", 'serv': 12, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/Q8LZSX4D/vegetarian-mushroom-shepherd-s-pie-with-vegan-version', 'cui': 'english', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10011355', 'name': 'skin potatoes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'kg', 'raw': '1 kg red skin potatoes'}, {'iid': 's_98965', 'name': 'soy granules', 'qty': 100.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '100g soy granules'}, {'iid': 's_11260', 'name': 'mushrooms', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'kg', 'raw': '1 kg mushrooms'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrot', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 carrot'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 red bell pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onions', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 onions, diced'}, {'iid': 's_2045', 'name': 'dill', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch of dill, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch of parsley, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_18375', 'name': 'eggs', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 eggs ( or egg substitutes for vegans, you can also add 3-4 tbsp dry yeast flakes)'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'sea salt, to taste'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/2 tsp ground pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1002028', 'name': 'paprika', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp sweet paprika'}, {'iid': 's_2049', 'name': 'thyme', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp dry thyme'}, {'iid': 's_4584', 'name': 'unrefined sunflower oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 tbsp unrefined sunflower oil'}]}, {'rid': 's_715391', 'title': 'Slow Cooker Chicken Taco Soup', 'inst': 'Once you have all of your ingredients added, allow it to cook all day for 8 hours on low. If you are wanting to make this a little faster, turn it on high and cook for 4 hours.When your Chicken Taco Soup is ready to serve, add in some crushed tortilla shells, shredded cheddar cheese, and a little sour cream.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/slow-cooker-chicken-taco-soup-recipe/', 'cui': 'mexican', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_16018', 'name': 'black beans', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 (15 oz.) can black beans'}, {'iid': 's_10011885', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 20.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '2 (10 oz.) cans diced tomatoes with green chilis'}, {'iid': 's_10011693', 'name': 'canned tomatoes', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 (15 oz.) can diced tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_43112', 'name': 'chili beans', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 (15 oz.) can chili beans'}, {'iid': 's_11168', 'name': 'kernal corn', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 (15 oz.) can whole kernal corn'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large red onion (finely chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_1055062', 'name': 'chicken breasts', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 boneless skinless chicken breasts (cut into 1" cubes)'}]}, {'rid': 's_636230', 'title': 'Broccoli with cheese soup', 'inst': 'Add onions and carrots to the melted butter and saute for 5-6 minutes over medium heat, or until vegetables are tender. Add 1 cup chicken broth and bring to the boil. Add broccoli and cook, covered, 5 to 6 minutes or until the broccoli is tender. Using a spoon, break broccoli florets in small pieces. Reduce heat to low and add remaining cup of chicken broth. Mix flour and milk in a small bowl and whisk until smooth. Add mixture to the pot. Add garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Continue cooking for about 5-6 minutes over low heat until soup thickens. Add cheese, handfuls at a time, and stir constantly over low heat for 10 minutes until smooth and creamy. If soup becomes too thick, add additional chicken stock. Do not let soup boil.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/ZYJG37NG/broccoli-with-cheese-soup', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10011090', 'name': 'broccoli florets', 'qty': 400.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '400 g broccoli florets'}, {'iid': 's_20081', 'name': 'flour', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '2 Tbs flour'}, {'iid': 's_1011077', 'name': 'milk', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup whole milk'}, {'iid': 's_1022020', 'name': 'garlic powder', 'qty': 0.125, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '⅛ tsp garlic powder'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '¼ tsp salt'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'ground pepper', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '¼ tsp ground pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1019', 'name': 'feta cheese', 'qty': 50.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '50 g feta cheese, crumbled'}, {'iid': 's_11147', 'name': 'swiss chesee', 'qty': 50.0, 'unit': 'g', 'raw': '50 g Swiss chesee, coarsely grated'}]}, {'rid': 's_632347', 'title': 'Ancient Grains Bread', 'inst': 'In a large bowl or stand mixer, whisk together yeast, flours, rye flakes, flaxseed, amaranth, quinoa, soy flour, wheat gluten, skim milk powder and salt. Stir in warm water and honey, mixing thoroughly to form a cohesive, fairly firm (but workable) dough. Turn out onto a floured board or knead with the dough hook for 12 minutes, until very elastic and smooth. Place into a bowl, cover and allow to rest 30 minutes. Roll rested dough into a log shape and tuck into a greased loaf pan. Cover with a clean towel and allow to rise 50-60 minutes. Preheat oven to 350F. Slash the top of the loaf 2-3 times with a sharp knife or lame. Bake 40 minutes. Turn out of pan immediately and cool on a rack before slicing', 'serv': 14, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/Y3ZZC68V/ancient-grains-bread', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10118375', 'name': 'yeast', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'package', 'raw': '1 package instant yeast'}, {'iid': 's_20081', 'name': 'flour', 'qty': 2.25, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 1/4 cups flour'}, {'iid': 's_20080', 'name': 'flour', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup whole wheat flour'}, {'iid': 's_98905', 'name': 'rye flakes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': 'cup rye flakes'}, {'iid': 's_12220', 'name': 'ground flaxseed', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons ground flaxseed'}, {'iid': 's_20001', 'name': 'amaranth grain', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons amaranth grain'}, {'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': 'cup quinoa'}, {'iid': 's_16115', 'name': 'soy flour', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup soy flour'}, {'iid': 's_48052', 'name': 'vital wheat gluten', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '1 1/2 tablespoons vital wheat gluten'}, {'iid': 's_1154', 'name': 'skim milk powder', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': 'cup skim milk powder'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'warm water', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': 'cups warm water'}, {'iid': 's_19296', 'name': 'honey', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup honey'}]}, {'rid': 's_1132339', 'title': 'Garlic Lemon Chili Broccoli', 'inst': 'Whatch video', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://foodwishes.blogspot.com/2010/06/will-this-great-broccoli-salad-become.html', 'cui': 'american', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11090', 'name': 'broccoli', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '1 1/2 pounds broccoli'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '3 cloves garlic, mashed'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 tbsp lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_1022053', 'name': 'rice vinegar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 tbsp rice vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_1002046', 'name': 'dijon mustard', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/2 tsp Dijon mustard'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 0.33333334, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/3 cup olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_1032009', 'name': 'red pepper flakes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'red pepper flakes to taste'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper to taste'}]}, {'rid': 's_659927', 'title': 'Shrimp and Avocado Salad', 'inst': 'Firstly, to cook the shrimp, heat the olive oil in a pan and once hot add the shrimp crushed garlic and chili flakes. It is important to get the oil nice and hot (not smoking, just before that point) your shrimp should sizzle when added to the pan. Check the back of the shrimp and when you see the colour change about half way up, turn them over. Do the same on the other side. This should only take a minute to two minutes maximum on both sides  otherwise you will get a rubbery result if you leave it too long. Squeeze over the lime juice  this too should bubble and reduce. Add a little salt and pepper, stir through, remove from the heat and set aside. Mix the dressing ingredients together, check for flavour, adjust if need be and set aside. Place all the salad ingredients in a bowl except the avocado and the salt and pepper. Prepare the avocado as you are about to serve otherwise it will turn brown. Once it is covered in the lime dressing, this will slow down the oxidization process and it wont go brown so easily. When you are ready to serve mix  of the avocado through the salad and add the dressing. Toss everything together. Taste to see if you need any salt and pepper. Place your shrimp on top of the salad with the rest of the avocado and sprinkle/pour any residue from the pan over your salad in which you cooked the shrimp. This is great flavour, so you dont want to lose it.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/ZTNWCWQP/shrimp-and-avocado-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_15270', 'name': 'the shrimp', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'The Shrimp'}, {'iid': 's_10015243', 'name': 'shrimp', 'qty': 600.0, 'unit': 'gr', 'raw': 'About 600gr of large tiger style shrimp (prawns/langoustine) peeled and cleaned'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 x garlic cloves, crushed'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 x tbsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_9160', 'name': 'juice of lime', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'Juice of 1 lime'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and Pepper'}, {'iid': 's_21052', 'name': 'the salad', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'The Salad'}, {'iid': 's_10111251', 'name': 'the of 1 cos lettuce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'leaves', 'raw': 'The leaves of 1 medium Cos lettuce finely shredded'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil leaves', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6/8 basil leaves chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10111168', 'name': 'corn', 'qty': 200.0, 'unit': 'gr', 'raw': '200gr sweet corn'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'spring onions', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 x spring onions (scallions) chopped finely'}, {'iid': 's_9266', 'name': 'pineapple', 'qty': 600.0, 'unit': 'gr', 'raw': '600gr fresh pineapple cut into small cubes'}, {'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocados into cubes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 x avocados chopped into cubes'}, {'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocado', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Avocado'}, {'iid': 's_43016', 'name': 'the dressing', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'The Dressing'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'tbsp olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 x tbsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_19296', 'name': 'tbsp honey', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 x tbsp honey'}, {'iid': 's_9160', 'name': 'juice of lime', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'Juice and zest of 3 limes'}]}, {'rid': 's_716217', 'title': 'Vietnamese Pancakes with Vegetables, Herbs and a Fragrant Dipping Sauce (Bánh Xèo)', 'inst': 'Begin by preparing the pancake batter. Whisk together the rice flour, egg, sea salt, turmeric, cayenne and green chili. Gradually whisk in the coconut milk. The mixture should be a smooth, semi-thick batter that is of pouring consistency. Add a little water if necessary. Cover and set aside while you prepare the rest of the food.Now prepare the sauce. Whisk together all of the ingredients and set aside.For the filling, combine the carrot, radish, green onions, green chilies and snow peas. Put the herbs in another bowl and have your sprouts ready along with the mushrooms. Heat a teaspoon of oil over medium heat in a non-stick skillet. When hot, ladle 1/2 cup of batter into the pan and spread with the bottom of the ladle until you have a roughly 6 to 8 inch pancake.  Fry for 6 to 8 minutes or until you have small holes forming and the bottom is crispy brown, then flip and fry for another few minutes on the other side. Transfer to a plate and keep warm in a 150 oven while you finish the rest of the pancakes  you should finish with 4 to 6 pancakes.To serve, scatter a portion of the vegetables, herbs and mushrooms over one half of the pancake. Sprinkle some sauce over top and fold the pancake. Drizzle with more sauce and there you go.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodandspice.com/2012/05/vietnamese-pancakes-with-vegetables.html', 'cui': 'vietnamese', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_20090', 'name': 'brown rice flour', 'qty': 1.3333334, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/3 cups brown rice flour'}, {'iid': 's_19334', 'name': 'brown sugar', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1/2 tablespoon brown sugar'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrot', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large carrot, scrubbed and grated'}, {'iid': 's_2031', 'name': 'cayenne', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': 'pinch of cayenne'}, {'iid': 's_12118', 'name': 'coconut milk', 'qty': 1.75, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 3/4 cups of coconut milk + water if needed'}, {'iid': 's_11430', 'name': 'daikon radish', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium daikon radish, scrubbed and grated'}, {'iid': 's_1123', 'name': 'egg', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 egg, beaten'}, {'iid': 's_11950', 'name': 'enoki mushrooms', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup enoki mushrooms, trimmed'}, {'iid': 's_2044', 'name': 'basil leaves', 'qty': 0.6666667, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '2/3 cup fresh basil leaves, roughly chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10211216', 'name': 'ginger', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'inch', 'raw': '1-inch piece fresh ginger, grated'}, {'iid': 's_2064', 'name': 'mint leaves', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup fresh mint leaves, trimmed and roughly chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10511297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup fresh parsley or cilantro, roughly chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic, crushed'}, {'iid': 's_31015', 'name': 'chili', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 fresh green chili, seeded and minced'}, {'iid': 's_31015', 'name': 'chilies', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 fresh green chilies, seeded and sliced into small strips'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'green onions', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 green onions, washed and cut on an angle'}, {'iid': 's_9160', 'name': 'juice of lime', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'juice from 2 limes'}, {'iid': 's_10011043', 'name': 'mung bean sprouts', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup mung bean sprouts (see note below)'}, {'iid': 's_10511819', 'name': 'chilies', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 fresh red chilies, seeded and minced'}, {'iid': 's_1022053', 'name': 'rice vinegar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon rice vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon sea salt'}, {'iid': 's_4058', 'name': 'sesame oil', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '1 1/2 tablespoons toasted sesame oil'}, {'iid': 's_4058', 'name': 'sesame oil', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'sesame oil for frying'}, {'iid': 's_11300', 'name': 'snow peas', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups snow peas, sliced into small strips'}, {'iid': 's_10116124', 'name': 'tamari sauce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon tamari sauce'}, {'iid': 's_2043', 'name': 'turmeric', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon turmeric'}]}, {'rid': 's_659109', 'title': 'Salmon Quinoa Risotto', 'inst': 'In a 4 quart saucepan, heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil over medium high heat. When oil is shimmering, add diced onion. Saute onion until transparent. Add quinoa to onion mixture and stir, to toast quinoa, for 2 minutes. Add 1 cup of vegetable stock to quinoa and onions. Stir until stock is absorbed.  Once stock is absorbed, add 1 cup of stock. Continue stirring until stock is absorbed. Add remaining stock in 1/2 cup intervals, stirring until all stock is absorbed. Remove from heat. While preparing the onion quinoa mixture, heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a saute pan with chopped garlic (over medium high heat). Once garlic is sizzling, add chopped kale to the pan. Turn kale to coat with oil and garlic. Turn kale mixture until fragrant (approximately 2 minutes). Remove kale mixture from heat. Once quinoa is complete, add kale and salmon. Stir to combine. Add salt and pepper to taste.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/KH5STR7N/salmon-quinoa-risotto', 'cui': 'mediterranean', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup Quinoa'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '1 medium Onion (diced)'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'kale', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'leaves', 'raw': '8 Leaves of Kale (stems removed and cut into ribbons)'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '5 Garlic Cloves (finely chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons Olive Oil (divided)'}, {'iid': 's_15076', 'name': 'poached salmon', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '10 ounces Poached Salmon (flaked)*'}, {'iid': 's_6615', 'name': 'vegetable stock', 'qty': 32.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '32 ounces Organic Vegetable Stock'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Pepper'}]}, {'rid': 's_644826', 'title': 'Gluten Free Dairy Free Sugar Free Chinese Chicken Salad', 'inst': 'For the salad:Finely slice the red, and green cabbage. Remove ends and finely slice romaine lettuce.Trim ends of scallions (white and green side) and finely slice.Peel and grate carrots, or put into a mini food processor to finely chop.Peel clementines then remove pith from slices. Add all the ingredients into a glass jar and shake until well blended, or whisk all the ingredients in a mixing bowl. Pour dressing over salad, toss to combine well.If making ahead, dress the salad just before serving.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/ZSNGMXBF/gluten-free-dairy-free-sugar-free-chinese-chicken-salad', 'cui': 'chinese', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2048', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'ml', 'raw': '1 tsp. (5ml) of organic apple cider vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon crushed black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10012023', 'name': 'sesame seeds', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '1 1/2 tablespoons black sesame seeds'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrots', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 carrots'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '1/4 C extra virgin olive oil + 7-8 Tbsp for frying'}, {'iid': 's_11109', 'name': 'cabbage', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 green cabbage'}, {'iid': 's_1082047', 'name': 'kosher salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon kosher salt'}, {'iid': 's_9218', 'name': 'satsuma mandarins', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6-8 fresh satsuma mandarins'}, {'iid': 's_11112', 'name': 'cabbage', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 red cabbage'}, {'iid': 's_5064', 'name': 'chicken breasts roasted', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 chicken breasts (bone in, preferably organic) roasted and shredded'}, {'iid': 's_10111251', 'name': 'romaine lettuce hearts', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'bunches', 'raw': '2 bunches romaine lettuce hearts'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'scallions', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 scallions'}, {'iid': 's_4058', 'name': 'sesame oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons sesame oil'}, {'iid': 's_93640', 'name': 'juice of 1 mandarin (cut crosswise then tablespoon into jar over a strainer)', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'juice of 1 mandarin (cut crosswise then tablespoon into jar over a strainer)'}, {'iid': 's_12023', 'name': 'sesame seeds', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons white sesame seeds'}, {'iid': 's_99005', 'name': 'xylitol', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '1 1/2 tablespoons xylitol (I use Epic Dental brand)'}]}, {'rid': 's_1000566', 'title': 'Easy Instant Pot Beef Tips and Rice', 'inst': 'Set Instant Pot to the saute setting. Once warm, add olive oil, beef tips, and onion. Stir and saut for 5 minutes or until meat starts to brown. Add water, Dales, and cream of mushroom soup, and garlic powder. Stir to mix well, and then cover with lid. Cook on Manual Setting on High Pressure for 25 minutes. It will take a few minutes to come to pressure. Once done, allow to naturally release for 20 minutes. Serve over rice (or sub noodles or mashed potatoes) and serve with french bread to sop up the gravy.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/beef-tips-and-rice/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_23653', 'name': 'sirloin beef tips', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '2 pounds of sirloin beef tips'}, {'iid': 's_6147', 'name': 'cream of mushroom soup', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large can', 'raw': '1 large can (or 2 small cans) cream of mushroom soup'}, {'iid': 's_1022020', 'name': 'garlic powder', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp garlic powder'}, {'iid': 's_99288', 'name': "dale's seasoning sauce", 'qty': 0.33333334, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': "1/3 cup of Dale's Seasoning Sauce (or 1/3 cup of Worcestershire and 1 tsp black pepper)"}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '½ medium onion finely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup water'}]}, {'rid': 's_664786', 'title': 'Venison Stew', 'inst': 'Cut all ingredients into 1 inch pieces. Dredge venison with flour and spices. Brown venison in hot vegetable oil. Boil and simmer venison 2 hours with beef bouillon and water. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour. Mix 3 tablespoons flour and 1 cup cold water and add to stew to thicken.', 'serv': 7, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/JJ7SSGCX/venison-stew', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10023618', 'name': 'venison stew meat', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '2 pounds venison stew meat, cut in cubes'}, {'iid': 's_11960', 'name': 'baby carrots 4 stalks celery 1 can mushrooms 1 piece pepper 1 cup flour and 3 tbsp 2 tablespoons bee', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': 'Spices: onion salt, 8 cups water 4 pieces large potatoes 1 piece large onion 4 pieces carrots or baby carrots 4 stalks celery 1 can mushrooms 1 piece green pepper 1 cup flour and 3 tbsp 2 tablespoons beef bouillon'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '8 cups water'}, {'iid': 's_11352', 'name': 'potatoes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'pieces', 'raw': '4 pieces large potatoes'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'piece', 'raw': '1 piece large onion'}, {'iid': 's_11960', 'name': 'baby carrots', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'pieces', 'raw': '4 pieces carrots or baby carrots'}, {'iid': 's_11143', 'name': 'celery', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'stalks', 'raw': '4 stalks celery'}, {'iid': 's_11264', 'name': 'mushrooms', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'can', 'raw': '1 can mushrooms'}, {'iid': 's_11333', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'piece', 'raw': '1 piece green pepper'}, {'iid': 's_20081', 'name': 'flour and 3 tbsp', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup flour and 3 tbsp'}, {'iid': 's_1016008', 'name': 'beef bouillon', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons beef bouillon'}]}, {'rid': 's_657719', 'title': 'Radish & Snap Pea Quinoa Salad', 'inst': 'Make the quinoa: combine the quinoa and water in a sauce pan and bring to a boil.  Reduce the heat to a simmer (medium-low), stir the quinoa, then cover it and cook for 10 to 15 minutes until all of the water has been absorbed. Remove it from the heat, let it sit for 5 minutes, then fluff it up with a fork.  Cool the quinoa a bit before making the salad.  The quinoa can be made several days in advance and kept in the fridge if needed before using. Combine the yogurt, tahini, lemon juice, and a pinch of sea salt in a bowl and whisk until smooth.  Thin the dressing out with a bit of water if it is too thick.  Set aside. Combine the quinoa, snap peas, radishes, and parsley in a bowl. Pour over about half of the dressing, then toss to combine.  Taste the salad and add more dressing or sea salt if desired.  Enjoy at room temperature or chilled.  Makes 3 to 4 main dish servings or 6 to 8 side servings.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/684WRQ6L/radish-snap-pea-quinoa-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup quinoa, rinsed'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups water'}, {'iid': 's_10011300', 'name': 'snap peas', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pint', 'raw': '1 pint snap peas, cut in half (about 2 cups total)'}, {'iid': 's_11429', 'name': 'radishes', 'qty': 7.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '7 or 8 medium radishes, sliced'}, {'iid': 's_10211297', 'name': 'flat leaf parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large handful', 'raw': 'large handful of flat leaf parsley, minced'}, {'iid': 's_1001116', 'name': 'yogurt', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup plain yogurt (cultured coconut milk is my favorite option, but any plain yogurt will work)'}, {'iid': 's_12698', 'name': 'tahini', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 tbsp tahini'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'juice of lemon', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': 'juice of 1/2 a lemon'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'sea salt to taste'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'water as needed'}]}, {'rid': 's_659143', 'title': 'Salmon, Watercress, Fennel and Baby Beetroot Salad With Lemony "Caviar" Dressing', 'inst': 'Place the salmon in a pan, cover with water, and add the wine, bay and tarragon stalks.  Bring to the boil and then immediately turn off and leave for a couple of minutes to cook in the residual heat. Remove to a plate with a slotted spoon and leave to cool before flaking into large pieces.Make the dressing by lightly whisking the olive oil and lemon juice together. Stir in the Arnkha MSC and season with some black pepper.Next, arrange the watercress, beets and fennel in 4 shallow salad bowls, then add the salmon and tarragon. Drizzle over the Arnkha MSC dressing and serve.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/WHSTLX2T/salmon-watercress-fennel-and-baby-beetroot-salad-with-lemony-arenkha-msc-dressing', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'primal', 'pescatarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10015072', 'name': 'arënkha msc caviar substitute', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'raw': '4 teaspoons Arënkha MSC caviar substitute'}, {'iid': 's_10111080', 'name': 'baby beets', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '12 cooked baby beets'}, {'iid': 's_2004', 'name': 'bay leaf', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 bay leaf'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'freshly ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '6 tbsp extra virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11957', 'name': 'fennel', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'head', 'raw': '1 head fennel, outside leaves discarded, finely sliced'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 tbsp lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_10115076', 'name': 'salmon fillets', 'qty': 16.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '4 110g (4oz) skinless salmon fillets'}, {'iid': 's_2041', 'name': 'tarragon stalks', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'tarragon stalks'}, {'iid': 's_2041', 'name': 'tarragon leaves', 'qty': 9.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'few tarragon leaves'}, {'iid': 's_11591', 'name': 'watercress', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch watercress, picked over, washed & dried'}, {'iid': 's_14106', 'name': 'white wine', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon white wine'}]}, {'rid': 's_645978', 'title': 'Ground Turkey Stuffed Peppers', 'inst': 'Cook rice then knead it together with remaining filling ingredients. Cut tops off peppers and fill each one. Place in your slow cooker or a large stove-top pot. Mix together sauce ingredients. Top each stuffed pepper with sauce and pour remaining sauce all around the stuffed peppers. Cook on medium/low for about an hour. Top with grated parmesan cheese and a little parsley for looks and serve warm.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/VKY3BZ5J/ground-turkey-stuffed-peppers', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell peppers', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 bell peppers (choose your favorite color!)'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11549', 'name': 'tomato sauce', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 (8oz) can tomato sauce'}, {'iid': 's_10011693', 'name': 'canned tomatoes', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 (8oz) can diced tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_2029', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 tbsp dried parsley'}, {'iid': 's_1123', 'name': 'eggs', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 eggs'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp minced garlic'}, {'iid': 's_10023572', 'name': 'ground beef', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '1/2 lb ground beef'}, {'iid': 's_5662', 'name': 'ground turkey', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '1/2 lb ground turkey'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 onion, diced'}, {'iid': 's_1032', 'name': 'parmesan cheese', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup grated parmesan cheese'}, {'iid': 's_20444', 'name': 'rice', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup uncooked rice'}, {'iid': 's_19335', 'name': 'sugar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 heaping tbsp sugar'}, {'iid': 's_10011693', 'name': 'tomato soup', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 (8oz) can tomato soup'}, {'iid': 's_6971', 'name': 'worcestershire sauce', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce'}]}, {'rid': 's_715544', 'title': 'Brown Butter Twice Baked Sweet Potatoes', 'inst': 'Preheat your oven to 400 degrees F. Poke your sweet potatoes with a fork and place them directly on the rack of your oven. Place a piece of foil on the rack below to reduce mess. Bake the sweet potatoes for 45-50 minutes or until tender. Times may vary depending on how hot your oven gets. Remove the potatoes from the oven and let stand at room temperature until they are cool enough to handle, about 20-30 minutes. Leave the oven on.While your potatoes are cooling, melt the butter over medium heat. Continue to cook the butter, stirring frequently, until brown bits begin to form on the bottom of the pan, about 5-6 minutes. Pay close attention as the butter can quickly go from brown to burnt in a matter of seconds. Once you see the brown bits forming and a nutty aroma fills the air, pull the butter from the heat immediately. Set aside. Cut the tops off of the sweet potatoes, lengthwise. Scoop the sweet potato flesh into a medium bowl, leaving the skins in tact. To the bowl, add the brown butter, 2 tablespoons of the fresh parsley, 3/4 of the chopped bacon, and 4 ounces of the goats cheese. Sprinkle with salt and black pepper to taste and mash the ingredients together until combined. Scoop the filling back into the sweet potatoes. Place the potatoes on a baking sheet that has been lined with foil or parchment paper. Place them back in the oven to bake for 25 minutes.While your potatoes are baking for a second time, prepare your avocado cream. In the bowl of your food processor or blender, combine the avocados, sour cream and buttermilk. Add a dash of salt and pepper and pulse until completely smooth and creamy.Once your potatoes have baked, remove from oven. Sprinkle on the remaining parsley, bacon and goats cheese. Drizzle with avocado cream and serve immediately.Enjoy!I hope you enjoy this recipe for brown butter twice baked sweet potatoes!', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.pinkwhen.com/brown-butter-twice-baked-sweet-potatoes/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'primal'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_9037', 'name': 'avocados', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 very ripe avocados, pitted and skins removed'}, {'iid': 's_1230', 'name': 'buttermilk', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons buttermilk'}, {'iid': 's_10862', 'name': 'bacon', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'strips', 'raw': '4 strips of bacon, cooked until crisp and chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10511297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup fresh parsley, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1159', 'name': "goat's cheese", 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': "6 ounces goat's cheese, crumbled"}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1001256', 'name': 'cream', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup sour cream (plain Greek yogurt may be substituted)'}, {'iid': 's_11507', 'name': 'sweet potatoes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '4 medium sweet potatoes'}, {'iid': 's_1145', 'name': 'butter', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '6 tablespoons unsalted butter'}]}, {'rid': 's_716364', 'title': 'Rice and Peas with Coconut Curry Mackerel', 'inst': 'Pour 1 cup of coconut milk in a pot with 1 seasoning cube and allow to boil for a minute. Pour in your rice and peas in the boiling coconut milk and pour 2 cups of water and leave to boil till the rice and peas are soft on low heat.In a separate pot, season and bring the mackerel to boil in the rest of the coconut milk, curry powder and some water.Toss in the chopped onion, scotch bonnet peppers and garlic and allow to simmer on medium heat.Once the fish is cooked, add the corn starch to thicken the sauce and allow to simmer for 4 minutes on low heat. Serve with the rice and peas', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.afrolems.com/2014/10/31/rice-and-peas-with-coconut-curry-mackerel/', 'cui': 'indian', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_12118', 'name': 'coconut milk', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups of coconut milk'}, {'iid': 's_20027', 'name': 'corn starch', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon of corn starch'}, {'iid': 's_2015', 'name': 'curry powder', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons of curry powder'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove of garlic (chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_99186', 'name': 'seasoning cubes', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Seasoning cubes'}, {'iid': 's_15050', 'name': 'mackerel', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'medium piece', 'raw': '1 medium piece of Mackerel (chopped in 4 pieces)'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'bulb of onion', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 bulb of onion'}, {'iid': 's_10016033', 'name': 'kidney beans', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup of red kidney beans'}, {'iid': 's_20444', 'name': 'rice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of Rice'}, {'iid': 's_10011819', 'name': 'scotch bonnet peppers', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 scotch bonnet peppers'}]}, {'rid': 's_633226', 'title': 'Baby Bok Choy Stir Fry', 'inst': 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium high heat. Add shallots and cook 3  4 minutes to soften. Add bok choy, leaving leafy pieces aside. Cook another 3  4 minutes until crisp tender. Add remaining ingredients except almonds. Top with almonds.', 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/4KHXC282/baby-bok-choy-stir-fry', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11116', 'name': 'bok choy', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound bok choy, cleaned and chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11677', 'name': 'shallot', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '2 large shallot, sliced'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic'}, {'iid': 's_4047', 'name': 'coconut oil', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1/2 tablespoon coconut oil'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': '1 pinch salt'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': '1 pinch pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1032009', 'name': 'pepper flakes', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pinch', 'raw': '1 pinch red pepper flakes'}, {'iid': 's_12061', 'name': 'almonds', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons almonds, toasted'}]}, {'rid': 's_641422', 'title': 'Delightful Kale and Cabbage Slaw', 'inst': 'In a very large bowl, combine cabbage, kale, celery, scallion and carrot. Toss well. In a small bowl, combine dressing ingredients. Pour dressing over vegetables and toss to coat.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/RLKY3W3V/delightful-kale-and-cabbage-slaw', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11109', 'name': 'cabbage', 'qty': 5.0, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '5 c shredded green cabbage'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'kale', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '3 c shredded kale'}, {'iid': 's_11143', 'name': 'celery', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '1 c celery, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'scallion', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '3/4 c scallion, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrot', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '2 c carrot, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_43016', 'name': 'dressing', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Dressing'}, {'iid': 's_1022068', 'name': 'red wine vinegar', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '1/4 c red wine vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_1002024', 'name': 'mustard', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '1/2 t dry mustard'}, {'iid': 's_19912', 'name': 'agave nectar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '1 t agave nectar'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '1/4 t salt'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 't', 'raw': '3 T olive oil'}]}, {'rid': 's_631868', 'title': '4 Ingredient Chicken Pot Pie', 'inst': "Let the pie crusts stand at room temperature for 15 minutes or until they're easy to handle. Place 1 pie crust into a 9-inch pie plate. Stir the gravy, vegetables and chicken in a medium bowl. Spoon the chicken mixture into the pie plate. Place the remaining pie crust over the filling. Press the edges to seal. Cut several slits in the top crust. Bake at 400F. for 45 minutes or until the crust is golden brown. Use a combination of sliced carrots, peas and cubed potatoes.", 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/V7VFKMB2/chicken-pot-pie-with-swanson-chicken', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_18334', 'name': 'pie crust', 'qty': 15.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '1 package (15 ounces) refrigerated pie crust (2 crusts)'}, {'iid': 's_6999', 'name': "campbell's chicken gravy", 'qty': 10.5, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': "1 can (10 1/2 ounces) Campbell's Chicken Gravy"}, {'iid': 's_11583', 'name': 'cut-up vegetables', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '3 cups cooked cut-up vegetables *'}, {'iid': 's_5062', 'name': 'cans swanson premium chicken breast in water', 'qty': 9.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 ounces cans (4.5 each) Swanson Premium White Chunk Chicken Breast in Water, drained'}]}, {'rid': 's_633711', 'title': 'Baked Penne', 'inst': 'Preheat the oven to 400*. Chop butternut squash into 1" pieces and roast on a baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray until lightly browned, about 30-40 minutes. Once the squash is done baking, reduce heat to 350*. Bring a pot of water to a boil and cook pasta according to package directions, using the shortest recommended cooking time. While pasta is cooking, saute onions and mushrooms. In a food processor, combine about 1 cup roasted butternut squash cubes, tomato paste, jalapeo, water, nutritional yeast, garlic powder, salt, black pepper, and Italian seasoning until well blended. Mix with drained pasta, onions, mushrooms and kale. Spray a 9"x13" pan with cooking spray and pour pasta mixture into pan. Bake uncovered at 350* for 30 minutes.', 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/VVH5Y7PG/baked-penne', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11485', 'name': 'butternut squash', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small butternut squash, peeled& seeded'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1/2 large onion, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11266', 'name': 'baby portobella mushrooms', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 baby portobella mushrooms, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11120420', 'name': 'penne pasta', 'qty': 12.0, 'unit': 'ounces', 'raw': '12 ounces penne pasta (I used Garden Delight, any would work)'}, {'iid': 's_11887', 'name': 'tomato paste', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup tomato paste'}, {'iid': 's_11979', 'name': 'jalapeño pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 jalapeño pepper, chopped& partially seeded (depends how hot you want it!)'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup water'}, {'iid': 's_93690', 'name': 'nutritional yeast', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': 'cup nutritional yeast'}, {'iid': 's_1022020', 'name': 'garlic powder', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon garlic powder'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1022027', 'name': 'seasoning', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon Italian seasoning'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'kale', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups kale, chopped'}]}, {'rid': 's_655573', 'title': 'Penne Arrabiata', 'inst': 'Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Saute about 1 teaspoon of dried red pepper in a 3 tbsp. olive oil. Add 5 cloves fresh minced garlic, 2 tbsp.Fresh Italian parsley, minced.When these ingredients are not, but not smoking, add 1 can tomatoes, chopped. (I like Pomi tomatoes which comes in a box). Stir, cover and cook untilthe sauce i heated. Cook the Penne in salted boiling water. Cook until al dante. Drain and add to sauce. Mix throughly Just before serving, add some coarsely chopped fresh basil and a little more parsley. Serve immediately.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/2Y82DVJR/penne-arrabiata', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10011531', 'name': 'tomato', 'qty': 14.5, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 can (14 1/2 oz) whole tomato, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10511297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons parsley, fresh, minced'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 Cloves garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons Olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11120420', 'name': 'pkt penne', 'qty': 14.0, 'unit': 'oz', 'raw': '1 pkt (14 oz) Penne (pasta quills)'}, {'iid': 's_11821', 'name': 'peppers', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 dried red peppers'}]}, {'rid': 's_641387', 'title': 'Delicious Creamy Lentils and Chestnuts Soup', 'inst': 'Put the lentils in a large pot and cover with water. Add the onions, garlic, potato, tomatoes, chestnuts, bay leaf, salt and pepper and a tablespoon of olive oil. Cook for about 20 minutes and adjust with salt and pepper if necessary. Let it sit and cool down for 15 minutes. Remove the bay leaf. To obtain a creamy velvety consistency use  an electric immersion blender .', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/6NB227RW/delicious-creamy-lentils-and-chestnuts-soup', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_2004', 'name': 'bay leaf', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 bay leaf'}, {'iid': 's_12098', 'name': 'roasted chestnuts', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup of roasted chestnuts'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove or garlic minced'}, {'iid': 's_10316069', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups dry lentils'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 onion chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11352', 'name': 'potato', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 potato'}, {'iid': 's_10311529', 'name': 'roma tomatoes', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup of sweet cherry tomatoes or Roma tomatoes chopped'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Salt and pepper'}]}, {'rid': 's_638626', 'title': 'Chimichurri Skirt Steak with Grilled Asparagus', 'inst': 'Place all chimichurri sauce ingredients except for the olive oil in a food processor &amp; pulse until well chopped. While the food processor is going, slowly pour the olive oil into the mixture until blended.  Reserve half of the sauce to serve on the side with the meal.Season skirt steaks with salt &amp; pepper on bother sides.  Spoon the remaining chimichurri sauce over the steaks &amp; let marinate for 30 minutes up to overnight.Pre-heat the grill to 350 to 400 F.In a plastic resealable bag, add asparagus, olive oil, garlic, salt &amp; pepper.  Shake to coat &amp; place in a grill basket. Place the steak &amp; grill basket of asparagus directly over a hot grill.  Gently toss the asparagus for even grilling &amp; baste with garlic, olive oil mixture  10 minutes.Grill the skirt steak to desired temperature  5 to 8 minutes per side. Remove from grill &amp; let steak rest for 10 minutes before slice long strips.  Spoon reserved chimichurri sauce over steak &amp; serve with asparagus on the side.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/3VXHGQB6/chimichurri-skirt-steak-with-grilled-asparagus', 'cui': 'south american', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'ketogenic'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10011011', 'name': 'asparagus', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound green or white asparagus, woody ends snapped off & discarded'}, {'iid': 's_11819', 'name': 'chili pepper flakes', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/2 teaspoon chili pepper flakes'}, {'iid': 's_10311297', 'name': 'flat leaf parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup flat leaf parsley, lightly packed & rough chopped'}, {'iid': 's_2064', 'name': 'mint leaves', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '¼ cup fresh mint leaves'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'to 5 garlic cloves', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 to 5 garlic cloves, rough chopped'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 garlic cloves, peeled'}, {'iid': 's_1082047', 'name': 'kosher salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Kosher salt'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup of extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_2027', 'name': 'oregano leaves', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '¼ cup fresh oregano leaves'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon freshly ground pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'freshly cracked pepper', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Freshly cracked black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_1022068', 'name': 'red wine vinegar', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons Red wine vinegar'}, {'iid': 's_11677', 'name': 'shallot', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons shallot, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_23232', 'name': 'skirt steaks', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 skirt steaks'}]}, {'rid': 's_655706', 'title': 'Peppery Absorption-Cooked Red-Wine Capellini', 'inst': 'Preheat the oven to 375F. Break the capellini into approximately 3-inch lengths. Spread the pasta on a baking sheet, slide it into the oven, and toast, tossing occasionally with tongs, until golden brown, about 12 minutes. Meanwhile, heat the olive oil in a large pot (at least 5 1/2 quarts) with a lid over medium heat. Add the onion, garlic, and a pinch of salt and cook, allowing them only to soften and grow aromatic but not brown, about 5 minutes. Increase the heat to medium-high and add the zucchini and another pinch of salt. Saut until the zucchini is well browned, about 5 more minutes. Place the noodles on top of the zucchini mixture. Layer the asparagus and 1 cup of the cherry tomatoes on top of that and sprinkle in the smoked paprika, black pepper, cayenne pepper, oregano, and rosemary. Pour the red wine and  cup of water over the top. Toss as best you can with tongs; it will be hard at first because the noodles are stiff. Return the heat to medium and cover the pot. Every 3 minutes, remove the lid and toss the pasta. The total cooking time will be 8 to 12 minutes. Toward the end, taste a noodle each time you remove the lid to see if it is done. If not, and there isnt any moisture left on the bottom of the pot, add a bit more wine or water, about 1/3 cup. When the noodles are done to your liking, taste and make any final adjustments to the seasoning. Transfer to serving bowls. Garnish with the remaining 1/2 cup cherry tomatoes, the parsley, and another grind of black pepper. Serve immediately.', 'serv': 4, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/7H36QLRW/peppery-absorption-cooked-red-wine-capellini', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['dairy free'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10020420', 'name': 'angel hair pasta', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'pound', 'raw': '1 pound capellini or angel hair pasta'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'half alarge onion', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Half alarge white onion, thinly sliced'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 6.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '6 garlic cloves, minced'}, {'iid': 's_1082047', 'name': 'kosher salt', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'Kosher salt'}, {'iid': 's_11477', 'name': 'zucchini', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'pounds', 'raw': '1 ½ pounds zucchini, diced'}, {'iid': 's_11011', 'name': 'asparagus', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch asparagus, trimmed and cut into 1/2-inch lengths'}, {'iid': 's_10311529', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/2 cups halved cherry tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_1012028', 'name': 'paprika', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon smoked paprika'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_2031', 'name': 'cayenne pepper', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon cayenne pepper'}, {'iid': 's_2027', 'name': 'oregano leaves', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons fresh oregano leaves'}, {'iid': 's_2063', 'name': 'rosemary', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon minced fresh rosemary'}, {'iid': 's_14096', 'name': 'red wine', 'qty': 1.25, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/4 cups red wine (I use an inexpensive Spanish Tempranillo), plus additional as needed'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 1.25, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1 1/4 cups water, plus additional as needed'}, {'iid': 's_11297', 'name': 'flat parsley leaves', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'leaf', 'raw': 'Minced fresh flatleaf parsley leaves for garnish'}]}, {'rid': 's_661122', 'title': 'Spicy lentil and black rice soup with kale, spinach and leek', 'inst': "Start by soaking your beautiful green lentils in water while you dice up all of your veggies.While your lentils are soaking in the water, chop up your  carrots, celery, garlic, onion and leek.Once all your veggies are chopped, heat up the olive oil in a stock pot over medium high heat and add the diced veggies.  Cook just until the the onion and garlic softens, about 7 minutes or so.While your veggies are cooking, chop up your kale and get it ready to go, but don't add it yet.  You don't need to worry about chopping the spinach leaves, when it comes time to add them, just use the whole leaf.Once your veggies are cooked, drain your lentils and add them and the rice to the veggies. If you can't find a black rice, just use wild rice.Give the veggies, rice and lentils a stir and then add your veggie broth, water, kale, spinach and all of the spices and turn the heat to high.Keep the burner on high just until the soup boils, reduce the heat to low and cover for 25 minutes. Covering the soup will ensure that the lentils and rice cook thoroughly.After the soup cooks covered for 25 minutes, remove the cover and continue to cook on low for another 30 minutes or so.  I added another 1/2 tsp of salt and a bit of pepper for flavoring at this point and it was a perfect balance.After the final 30 minutes of simmer, simply serve and enjoy!", 'serv': 12, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/CWDP84PH/spicy-lentil-and-black-rice-soup-with-kale-spinach-and-leek', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_10020036', 'name': 'rice', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup black rice'}, {'iid': 's_11124', 'name': 'carrot', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups diced carrot'}, {'iid': 's_2031', 'name': 'cayenne', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/4 tsp cayenne'}, {'iid': 's_10111143', 'name': 'celery stalks', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '2 celery stalks (diced)'}, {'iid': 's_2009', 'name': 'chili powder', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon chili powder'}, {'iid': 's_1002014', 'name': 'cumin', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp cumin'}, {'iid': 's_10216069', 'name': 'green lentils', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '2 cups green lentils'}, {'iid': 's_2042', 'name': 'thyme', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp dried thyme'}, {'iid': 's_10211215', 'name': 'garlic cloves', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '3 garlic cloves (minced)'}, {'iid': 's_11233', 'name': 'kale', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch kale (chopped - I used purple kale but you can use any type)'}, {'iid': 's_11246', 'name': 'leek', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 leek (sliced)'}, {'iid': 's_2027', 'name': 'oregano', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/2 tsp oregano'}, {'iid': 's_1002030', 'name': 'cracked pepper', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1 tsp cracked black pepper'}, {'iid': 's_10011282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1 red onion (diced)'}, {'iid': 's_1012047', 'name': 'sea salt', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '2 tsp sea salt'}, {'iid': 's_10011457', 'name': 'spinach', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1/2 bunch fresh spinach (chopped)'}, {'iid': 's_6615', 'name': 'vegetable broth', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '4 cups vegetable broth'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 10.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '10 cups water'}]}, {'rid': 's_1697645', 'title': 'Cauliflower Rice', 'inst': 'Cut cauliflower into chunks, rinse in colander, and pat dry. Pulse in the food processor for about 20 seconds. Over medium-high heat, heat up extra-vigin olive oil and sauté a finely chopped leek for 2 minutes. Add uncooked cauliflower rice and stir occasionally for about 4 minutes. If you cook the cauliflower rice for too long it’ll become a) mushy and b) bitter. Season with ¼ tsp each of salt and pepper. Toward the end, stir in parsley. Taste and re-season as necessary. Serve and garnish with some extra parsley.', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://maplewoodroad.com/cauliflower-rice-and-oven-roasted-cauliflower/', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'paleolithic', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal', 'whole 30', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11135', 'name': 'cauliflower', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'lb', 'raw': '1 (1-1/2 lb) head of cauliflower'}, {'iid': 's_1034053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbsp', 'raw': '2 Tbsp extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11246', 'name': 'leek', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '1 leek, finely chopped (about 1/2 c)'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'tsp', 'raw': '1/4 tsp each of salt and pepper (more to taste)'}, {'iid': 's_10311297', 'name': 'flat leaf parsley', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'c', 'raw': '1/2 c flat leaf Italian parsley, roughly chopped'}]}, {'rid': 's_635679', 'title': 'Borani Esfanaaj', 'inst': 'Drizzle the oil into a medium pan and saut the onion and garlic on medium-low heat until tender and the onions are almost see-through. Add the spinach and cook until leaves are wilted. Add salt and pepper Set aside to cool for about 15 minutes. In a small bowl mix together the drained yogurt and cooked spinach. Add any salt or pepper to taste. Cool in the fridge for at least another 45 minutes. Then enjoy!', 'serv': 8, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/F6BYJPMT/borani-esfanaaj', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'primal'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon of olive oil, or any oil you have on hand'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small onion, chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'clove', 'raw': '1 clove garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_11463', 'name': 'a package of spinach', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '4 cups fresh spinach or a package of frozen spinach, washed'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1/4 teaspoon salt'}, {'iid': 's_10211821', 'name': 'bell pepper', 'qty': 8.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'pepper to taste'}, {'iid': 's_1116', 'name': 'the yogurt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1 cup of the drained yogurt'}]}, {'rid': 's_657698', 'title': 'Quinoa, Tomato, Green Onion Side Salad', 'inst': "Put your quinoa and your water in a pan. Heat over medium heat until bubbling, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook for about 15 minutes or until all the water is absorbed.While your quinoa is cooking, get out and wash your green onions and tomatoes. Chop them roughly.Chop a lemon in half and squeeze one half's juice into a bowl, picking out the seeds. Let your quinoa cool. A little warm is fine. Add olive oil, lemon juice, and tomatoes and green onions to the pan. Stir. Add salt and pepper to your liking. Serve chilled", 'serv': 2, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/ZHJ4PP8P/quinoa-tomato-green-onion-salad', 'cui': '', 'diets': ['gluten free', 'dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_11291', 'name': 'green onions', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup minced green onions'}, {'iid': 's_9150', 'name': 'lemon', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 lemon'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tbs', 'raw': '2 Tbs. olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_20035', 'name': 'quinoa', 'qty': 0.75, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '3/4 cup uncooked quinoa'}, {'iid': 's_1102047', 'name': 'salt and pepper', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'servings', 'raw': 'salt and pepper'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'medium size', 'raw': '2 medium size tomatoes'}, {'iid': 's_14412', 'name': 'water', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1-1/2 cups water'}]}, {'rid': 's_642121', 'title': 'Easy Tabouleh', 'inst': 'Chop the vegetables and parsley finely. The restaurant version has the veggies diced fairly small and I wanted to stay true to that.Rinse the cracked wheat in a fine mesh sieve and let drain. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.', 'serv': 1, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/HC6SVFST/easy-tabouleh', 'cui': 'middle eastern', 'diets': ['dairy free', 'lacto ovo vegetarian', 'vegan'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_20012', 'name': 'bulgur', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/2 cup bulgur'}, {'iid': 's_11206', 'name': 'cucumbers', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '2 smalls cucumbers'}, {'iid': 's_10311297', 'name': 'flat leaf parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'bunch', 'raw': '1 bunch of flat leaf parsley'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice from a lemon', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': '', 'raw': '1/2 lemon juice from a lemon'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons of olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_2047', 'name': 'salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'serving', 'raw': 'Salt'}, {'iid': 's_11529', 'name': 'tomatoes', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'medium', 'raw': '2 medium tomatoes'}]}, {'rid': 's_665378', 'title': 'Winter Fattoush Salad', 'inst': 'Toast the pita: Preheat the oven to 350F. Whisk the oil, zaatar and salt in a small bowl. Lay the pita bread on a baking sheet and brush both sides with the oil. Saute the onions and oil in a small skillet until onions soften and begin to brown. Add the lentils and stir to blend. Stir in the garlic and parsley and remove from heat. Season with salt and pepper. Whisk the dressing ingredients in a bowl until fully combined. You can also use a handheld blender.Compose the salad: Toss the salad ingredients in a large bowl. Add the lentils and pita crisps. Drizzle with the dressing and toss again. Mound the salad on a serving platter. Top with feta cheese and sprinkle with sumac.', 'serv': 6, 'url': 'https://www.foodista.com/recipe/FWQFYDLT/winter-fattoush-salad', 'cui': 'middle eastern', 'diets': ['lacto ovo vegetarian'], 'ings': [{'iid': 's_19912', 'name': 'agave nectar', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon agave nectar'}, {'iid': 's_1019', 'name': 'feta cheese', 'qty': 0.25, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '1/4 cup feta cheese (optional)'}, {'iid': 's_10311297', 'name': 'flat leaf parsley leaves', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'cup', 'raw': '½ cup flat leaf parsley leaves (or a mix of parsley and mint)'}, {'iid': 's_11215', 'name': 'garlic', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'cloves', 'raw': '2 cloves garlic, minced'}, {'iid': 's_10211111', 'name': 'ground sumac', 'qty': 0.5, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '½ teaspoon ground sumac'}, {'iid': 's_1082047', 'name': 'kosher salt', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'raw': '1 teaspoon kosher salt'}, {'iid': 's_10011233', 'name': 'lacinato kale leaves', 'qty': 4.0, 'unit': '', 'raw': '4 fresh Lacinato kale leaves'}, {'iid': 's_9152', 'name': 'lemon juice', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '2 tablespoons lemon juice'}, {'iid': 's_10116069', 'name': 'lentils', 'qty': 1.5, 'unit': 'cups', 'raw': '1½ cups cooked lentils (many markets carry vacuum-packed, precooked lentils, or boil 1 cup dried brown lentils in 2 cups salted water until tender, then drain)'}, {'iid': 's_4053', 'name': 'olive oil', 'qty': 3.0, 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'raw': '3 tablespoons olive oil'}, {'iid': 's_11282', 'name': 'onion', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'small', 'raw': '1 small onion, coarsely chopped'}, {'iid': 's_11297', 'name': 'parsley', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'raw': '1 tablespoon minced parsley'}, {'iid': 's_10011205', 'name': 'persian cucumber', 'qty': 1.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '1 large organic English or Persian cucumber with skin (about 1 cup shredded)'}, {'iid': 's_18413', 'name': 'pita breads', 'qty': 2.0, 'unit': 'large', 'raw': '2 large pita breads'}, {'iid': 's_11429', 'name': 'radishes', 'qty'